animal.description:
Papa
Male - senior
Poodle mix
Born 2006-2008

Weight:  approx. 17 pounds
Adoption Fee:  $100

NMAF ADOPTION APPLICATION, found at www.nmaf.org/adopt/adoption-application.

Please complete an Adoption Application if you are interested in Papa.

Papasan, which is a venerable term of respect used in East Asia for an older gentleman, came to NMAF after he took ill and his family did not want to, or could not afford to, get medical care for him so instead took him to the shelter where he received everything he needed and is now doing oh-so well.  Fabulous NMAF foster, Andrea, spotted him and we were able to get him out quickly.  He was given all his shots, neutered, had a dental and a full set of bloodwork as well as x-rays of his spine and hips while at the shelter - all records will be transferred to his new adopter.  Our veterinarian checked him out thoroughly and indicated he is between 12 & 14 yrs. old and is doing really well, all things considered. We have started him on supplements for his arthritis, but he needs no other medications at this point.  He is a real trouper and a sweetheart on top of that, is potty trained and uses the doggie door in his foster home.  He has a sweet and loving disposition and just wants to be someone's shadow all day.  For the right senior-loving family, he would be an excellent companion and promises to give the remainder of his years and heart to them!

More Info:  Contact Jeanette at jeanette.debar@yahoo.com.

NMAF dogs cannot be adopted out of the greater Albuquerque / Santa Fe area.

Adoption Clinic Location:  PetSmart - Academy & Wyoming, Saturdays, 10:00 a.m. - 1:00 p.m. - Currently Suspended

Please visit our website at www.nmaf.org for more information.

animal.description:
Breed: Pit Bull/Husky mix
Sex: Neutered Male
DOB: ~12/24/2018
Weight: 68 lbs
Energy Level: Medium
Personality Type: Affectionate, Playful, Goofy, Big Baby!
History: Transferred from another shelter; stray
Good With: Dogs, Kids 8+ years
Ideal Home: Any home ready for a big, strong dog! No apartments, please.
Fence Requirements: Preferred.
Special Info:

The information we are providing for this animal was developed based on observations and assessments in a shelter or foster environment. We do our best to provide information that will help determine if the dog might be a good fit for you. Please note that behaviors may change in a home environment. We also ask our applicants to assume that any animal they adopt from us will need to be potty trained and learn house manners, although this is not always the case. Our online animal bios are designed to provide as much information as possible and answer some anticipated questions. We do not have the resources to respond to emails with more specific questions.

We are receiving an unusually high number of applications per pet at this time! Please follow the rules below to ensure your application is reviewed; pay attention closely to these instructions because applications will NOT be processed if they are not followed. Please keep in mind that dog/cat availability is currently changing by the hour; you will receive an email if the animal you are interested in is no longer available. New dogs become available almost every day, so feel free to let us know if someone else interests you if your initial choice is already adopted! 

Fill out the application (DOG: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/IHD-DOG-Application-9-10-18.pdf, CAT: https://www.iheartdogs.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/IHD-CAT-Application.pdf) completely. Every question must be answered, and it must be signed. If you are going to type your responses, open the application, save it, type your answers, and save it again. 

-Applicants must be 21+ years old and live within a 50-mile radius of our shelter at 22415 Groesbeck Hwy, Warren 48089.

-You must identify at least 1 dog/cat that you are interested in. If there are multiple dogs/cats, number them in order of priority. 

-Scan a copy of proof of home ownership (i.e. tax bill, deed, or mortgage payment - you can black out the account #, etc.) or animal clause/agreement of your rental agreement.

-Attach the application and home ownership proof/rental agreement animal clause to a new email and send it to bark@iheartdogs.org. The subject line must be formatted to read ""#1 choice of dog/cat, Your First and Last Name"". Example: Subject: Fido, Jane Doe
Once your application is received, it will be assigned to an Adoption Counselor who will follow-up with the applicant who is the best fit within a few days, or to discuss other dogs/cats. It could take up to a couple of weeks for you to receive a final disposition on your application so there is no need to check on the status.

-Introductions will be scheduled by appointment only, 45 minutes per appointment. The entire household, including current dogs, must be present for the appointment. The introductions will take place outside in our parking lot.

-We will continue to perform vet checks for current and prior pets in the household.

-Home visits will be in person for the yard and virtual for inside the home.

-Finalizing the adoption will also be scheduled by appointment.

While this process may seem cumbersome, it is interim during COVID-19, and it is designed to help us respond to the volume of emails we receive every day. Since we are receiving a high volume of applications, please be patient if a dog/cat is no longer available. 

Thank you for your understanding.

animal.description:
Please read the animal bios completely before requesting additional information as we do our best to answer the most frequently ask questions in these bios. 

In order to adopt one of our animals an application must be submitted and approved. You can find these applications by going to http://humanemorgan.org/index.php?page=adoption 

ABOUT ADOPTING FROM THE HSMC: 
The shelter address is 1170 Fairground Rd. Madison, GA 30650. For more information on any of our pets, please feel free to email us at INFO@HUMANEMORGAN.ORG give us a call at 706-343-9977. 
All dogs are heartworm negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
All cats are FeLv/FIV negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
We are open 10am-5pm Monday-Saturday, we schedule our last adoption at 4pm everyday to allow our staff enough time to feed and walk dogs. 
We are an animal shelter and therefore are not able to individually potty train our residents. Many adult dogs do arrive ""house broken"" however due to animal behavior any change in environment will make an emotional impact on the animals and therefore initiate unwanted behaviors during the acclamation period. Please keep this in mind. Puppies do not have the biological maturity to maintain absolute bladder or bowel control and will require a certain degree of potty training and house breaking. Please consider the time and commitment it takes to provide the necessary building blocks for these special babies, prior to submitting your application. 
If you have any questions please email us at info@humanemorgan.org and provide name of the animal you are interested in, in the subject line. 
Thank you, HSMC Staff 

ADOPTION FEES Adoption Fees may change without notice. Always verify the fee when finalizing the adoption. 
~ Cats and Kittens ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $100 
* 1-5 Years = $75 
* Over 5 Years = $50 
** Purebred cats and kittens may be subject to special pricing 

~ Mix Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $200 
* 1 -3 Years = $175 
* 4-8 Years = $150 
* Over 8 Years = $100

~ Purebred and Designer Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $375 
* 1-3 Years = $350 
* 4-8 Years = $275 
* Over 8 Years = $150 

~ Medical and Special Needs ~ 
We have rescued dogs and cats which require additional medical care or that have special needs which are not life threatening. In these cases we may require a higher fee to help recoup the costs of their care while at our rescue.

animal.description:
Say hello to Madelyn. This senior girl found herself in the shelter after being confiscated from a neglect case. She has had a very hard life and just wants a safe, quiet place to snuggle up in a cozy dog bed and watch everything going on around her. Madelyn doesn't ask for much but quiet, some food and some space to just relax. This poor girl has clearly been neglected and frightens when you come near her. She will scurry away or nip if she feels threatened. In the first week with us she has started moving around more and even trying to jump on an elevated dog bed so she is feeling a bit better. Madelyn is definitely a super senior who just wants a quiet place for her final time here. She deserves some peace and love on her terms for once in her life.

NOTE: To adopt, please apply at polkadogz.org. All current pets must be spayed/neutered and up to date on vaccinations and heartworm prevention. We only adopt in Florida. All adoption fees go to help all the dogs in our rescue, manyh of which need major medical care. Thank you for caring for the greater good.

animal.description:
Meet Yayoki!

Yayoki is a sweet, affectionate little lady looking for a family to call her own! Yayoki loves to cuddle, but also enjoys going for adventures and exploring outside! She gets along with other dogs and walks well on a leash. She is a total lovebug and is ready to share her love with the world!

Yayoki's Story: Yayoki came to Soi Dog due to a road traffic accident. During her intake examination on entry the vet found that she had a right femoral neck fracture and a surgical femoral head and neck excision was performed to treat the injury. Now Yayoki is a healthy dog and has since recovered from those injuries. She has a slightly uneven gait and posture because her right hindlimb is shorter than her left leg due to the bone surgery which resulted in decreased bone length in Yayokis limb. It is important that Yayokis adopter remain vigilant for any signs of lameness and ensures that her weight is under control and a light exercise regime is followed to avoid putting any strain on her limbs.

Details: 
Gender: Spayed Female
Estimated Age: 3 years
Breed: Shepherd Mix
Weight: 35 lbs.

Yayoki will be traveling from Thailand and will be ready to go to her forever home in late February! 
To apply visit: https://www.rescueallthedogs.org/adopt-1

animal.description:
Meet Bobby Boy!

This dude has very unique coloring and eyes that will melt your heart! He has everyone stop and comment on how beautiful he is! 

 The best part about Bob is that he loves life, and he may have springs for legs. We like to refer to him as bouncy Bob! His joy is contagious. Who doesn't love to be around a happy dog? He zooms around the yard with joy, and will chase a ball with a wagging tail. 

Bob is a beautiful 2-year-old happy go lucky boy. He weighs 56 lbs and seems to be in perfect shape. He is happy to greet people and his tail never stops wagging! He is food motivated and will do anything for a treat, so training is made easier. He enjoys brain games like puzzle toys or eating his meals out of a slow feeder toy. He loves to have attention from his people! He has a soft side too. Bob is very sweet and loves to lay on his back for belly rubs. He looks up at you to tell you he's glad you're there with him. 

He needs a confident leader that will offer consistency and structure. Bob is looking for a home that is active and he would be a great running partner. He would like to be an only dog, probably no young kids because of his magnificent bouncing skills. 
He is able to coexist around other dogs at his training house but not freely socialize, so needs to be an only dog and will not be a dog park dog, but dog parks are risky anyway!

He is potty trained, Kennel trained, fully vaccinated, and neutered. He is one of a kind and loves to be around his people. He is great for basic grooming needs. Bob is currently at a training facility working on his basic obedience and leash skills and he is ready to get started on the right track for his forever home! He is doing great with training and the training team can show you all that he has learned and how to implement it at home. 

We would like for him to find a home that can embrace all his goofiness! For more information about Bob please email Jaime at jaime@threelittlepittiesrescue.org he is currently located in Vancouver, WA 

Apply here: https://petstablished.com/adoption_form/30283/generic

animal.description:
Molly is a super sweet girl who loves everyone she meet and loves being close to her person. Loves snuggling and giving kisses 

 

Although still learning how to walk on the leash, she has made amazing progress in just a few days. She does stop if there is something or someone new, but then greets them calmly and gently. She does need further exposure to new things. She is still learning her manners, and will need some patients and training as she likes to counter surf. She is not a barker and she is housetrained.



She loves playing with her sister Lily, they love to play and run around together and would do best in a home with a fenced yard; as walks alone does not burn off enough of her puppy energy and a home with another dog friend would be amazing. 



She is crate trained and we would recommend that she be crated when you are away from home - at least until you know she will not get into anything. 



If you are looking to add an energetic pup to your family, apply today to begin the adoption process. https://www.fluffanimalrescue.org/molly-s-page-f

animal.description:
Lily is super sweet and friendly, loves snuggling and giving kisses, has met many dogs and humans and loves everyone; although she may be a little shy and hesitant at first.



Although still learning how to walk on the leash has made amazing progress in just a few days. She does stop if there is something or someone new, but then greets calmly and gently. She does need further exposure to new things to help build her confidence. 

 

She is still learning her manners, and will need some patients and training as she likes to counter surf. She is not a barker and she is housetrained.



She loves playing with her sister, Molly; they love to play and run around together and would do best in a home with a fenced yard; as walks alone does not burn off enough of her puppy energy and a home with another dog friend would be amazing. 



She is crate trained and we would recommend that she be crated when you are away from home - at least until you know she will not get into anything. 



If you are looking to add an energetic pup to your family, apply today to begin the adoption process. www.fluffanimalrescue.org

NFASI is open Tuesday through Saturday 10am-4pm and hold adoption events periodically around the Pahrump area. Please call to confirm the pet you are interested in is still available (775) 537-8674 and onsite (or we can make arrangements for their Foster Parent to bring them in).

Foster homes & volunteers are always needed please contact us regarding how you can foster or volunteer for our organization.

animal.description:
Blackdog Club is a facility-based rescue. We are open to the public Wednesday-Sunday between 10-6. An appointment is not required. 

If an adopter wishes to bring a current pet for a meet/greet, please send vet records showing the pet is UTD on all vaccines prior to your visit to blackdogclub@outlook.com

The adoption fee includes spay or neuter, microchip, age-appropriate vaccines, rabies vaccine, fecal test, deworming, and heartworm test. Dogs are treated if heartworm positive. All dogs are UTD on heartworm/flea/tick prevention. All dogs are health screened and vaccinated by our vet, Family Pet Animal Hospital or Quality Care Animal Hospital.

We do not know if our dogs are house trained. They are crated overnight. 

Bella joined us from a very loving home. Her owners adored her; however, they could no longer care for her due to their medical issues. She is house and crate trained. We tested her with other dogs (see video) and she passed with flying colors. Cats are iffy. Estimated DOB: 04/18/2018. Current weight: 45 lbs. Please ensure you are familiar with this breed! They are not for everyone. Bella will not be adopted into apartment life.

Hello there, my name is Brazos! I'm the new kid in town coming all the way from Texas and I'm excited to be here! The people here are great but I don't know about all this snow and cold... brrr! I am about 2 years old and still have some puppy 
tendencies due to lack of 
consistency in my life. I love to run, play, chase, and give kisses. A training class would be fun and beneficial for the both of us! I look bigger in pictures than in person but I have just as much (if not more) love to give! What does a cute guy like me have to do to find a nice family around here? I'm ready!

Owner Experience Level: Some Experience
Cats: Yes
Dogs: Maybe/Maybe Not

animal.description:
Hey friends! My name is Rover. I'm 3 (almost 4) years old and about 50 pounds. I was surrendered recently because my family thought it would be in my best interest if they let me find a new home me so I wouldn't stray away from the farm again and get hurt. They did love me a lot and said I was a great dog so no hard feelings! I'm sweet, energetic, and love being around my people. Just think if you take me home you can sing the poem, ""I have a dog and his name is Rover, he is the one I love the best; When he is good he is good all over, when he is bad, he is just a pest"" But we can forget that last line because I am only a good boy!

	Approved Applicants may make the adoption fee payment by clicking donate above. Partial adoption fees will not hold a dog.

animal.description:
LOOKING FOR ADOPTIVE HOME ASAP IN NE/CO/WY

 

 HARLEY 

 

 Located in the Sidney, NE area 

 Harley is a Pit Bull

 Harley is 1.5

 Dog friendly 

 Cats friendliness unknown

 Kid friendly 

 House trained 

 Crate trained and know basic commands (sit, stay, lay down)

 Completely vetted 

 45-50 lbs approx 

 

We were contacted to help find new homes for these two amazing young dogs. Their current owner is having an extremely hard time with this decision, but she reached out to us because she knows we will make sure they go to the best possible homes. 

 

Their current owner has had them since small puppies; but the original dog in the home is increasingly not having it and she is concerned for their safety. We usually see owners give up the older dogs in these situations so we commend this owner for standing by her boy and doing what she feels is best for all involved. 

 

Both of these dogs are young and friendly and trained and completely vetted. I have no doubt we can find them each an amazing home. They do not need to go together. 

 

If interested in either Zeus or Harley please contact us! 

 

 To Contact Us 

 TEXT Cilena at 308-249-4308

 Message us through our website http://www.highplainspaw.org

 Message the Facebook Page at https://www.facebook.com/HighPlainsPAW

 Fill out our Adoption Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/adoption-application

 Fill out our Foster Application at https://www.highplainspaw.org/foster-application

 Email us at highplainspaw@gmail.com

 

 $200.00 Adoption Fee 

(Which is considered a non refundable donation and being we are a 501c3 organization it is tax deductible. The fee itself is not negotiable, our vets don't negotiate and thus neither do we).

 

 WE DO NOT HAVE A FACILITY ALL OUR DOGS ARE LOCATED IN FOSTER HOMES. This means there is no place for you to go in person to view our dogs. We ask that an application be filled out and we will go from there!

 

 Posted by Cilena

Oh, do I look like a familiar face? Well, guess what... I am! My name's Shania and Muddy Paws and I go way back... I was born on June 19, 2020 and my mama had a big 'ol litter of puppies. She didn't have enough milk to feed us all so me and four of my siblings came to Muddy Paws where we got bottle fed until we were big and strong. Once I could be out on my own I found a home but, well, I'm back at MP due to no fault of my own. I like my new foster family so much and I get to run outside in the backyard a lot! My foster mom says I'm still adjusting to the other big dog in my house so we haven't spent a lot of time playing together yet. I keep hearing people say, "she's a very smart girl" and I think they're talking about me! I know how to "sit," "come," and "shake," and I even know what "down" means. My foster mom says that structure and routine are important for a little one like me and I think she's right. For example, I pretty much know how to potty outside but sometimes I need a reminder. One of my favorite activities (besides playing) is to snuggle up with my family for a cozy night together on the couch... that makes me feel so loved and safe. I hope I can find a family that likes to learn and play and snuggle as much as me!

The suggested adoption donation for Shania is $450. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
We're fond of Farley! It's hard not to fall for that earnest face. Farley has a charming personality that he is showing off more and more as we get to know him. He has some silly, puppyish energy and is always excited to get out and about on walks. He seems quite curious and active, and enjoys sniffing around outside. He has a passion for treats, and seems like he already knows sit and down on command. He seems to have a goofy disposition with just a bit of puppyishness thrown in (at around 2 years old, he is still kind of a teenager.) But he also seems to have a sweet side, and we think will be very happy to be someone's best pal. Once he settles into an active routine we think he'll make a great companion! Farley is around 2 years old and weighs 62 lbs.
Farley unfortunately arrived at the kennel heartworm positive but the good news is that it is treatable. We'll cover the cost, Farley just needs to find a home where he can be on lower-activity and rest for a month and a half while he is recovering from the treatment when he gets it. Visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to find out more information and set up a meet with him!
Due to COVID-19, CITY DOGS is currently doing adoptions by APPOINTMENT ONLY. Please visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog to request a meet and greet! 

Questions? Email: citydogs@city.cleveland.oh.us | Call: (216) 664-3476
Visit: 9203 Detroit Avenue Cleveland, OH 44102

Hours:
10 AM - 3 PM Monday, Wednesday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday
10 AM - 6 pm Tuesday & Thursday

Fee: $61 | Includes spay/neuter, shots, microchip, license, 30 days free pet insurance (when registered upon adoption)

The CITY DOGS mission is to increase adoptions from the City Kennel by changing the image of the pit bulls who make up the majority of the kennel population, by preparing all adoptable dogs in the kennel for lives in loving homes and by creating as many opportunities as possible for the public to meet and get to know our dogs for the terrific pets they are meant to be.

Our Adoption Process...
Here's a little about how things work:
All of the CITY DOGS posted for adoption are available for direct adoption from the kennel, unless noted otherwise. You must schedule a meet with a dog in advance - we are not currently accepting walk-ins. Please look online first to see if there are any dogs you think would be a good fit for your home before scheduling a meet. To get the process started, visit www.tinyurl.com/meetacitydog and fill out the form. One of our adoption counselors will get in touch to schedule and confirm your meet! At the kennel, an adoption counselor will introduce you and your family to the adoptable dogs, share information we know about them, and discuss our suggested ways for successfully integrating a new dog into your home. You are welcome to meet multiple dogs. If the dog you adopt is already fixed, he or she may leave with you that day - otherwise, the dog can go home after receiving the spay or neuter surgery.)

About Our Dogs: All available dogs have gone through a behavioral and medical assessment. This assessment is a snapshot of who the dog is at that given time. We cannot make any guarantees with regard to behavior, temperament or health of any City Dog once they are in the home. Most of our dogs are picked up as strays, so we do not know what kind of home environment they were living in (i.e. with kids, other dogs or other cats), nor do we know if most of them are house trained. Everything we know about them is based on volunteer and staff observations. We do have some dogs in foster homes, where they will have more information about how the dog is in a home environment. It is very hard to tell with certainty whether or not a dog will be good with kids, cats or another dog. If you have kids in the home or another dog, we do require that they be present for a meet and greet with the dog you are considering for adoption.

Heath/Vaccinations: Dogs that are adopted directly from the kennel need to go to your personal vet within two weeks of leaving the kennel. All dogs receive their DAPPL, Rabies, and Bordatella vaccines, though you may be required to get follow up boosters. All dogs come microchipped and with a Cuyahoga County license.?

She can sometimes get into things she's not supposed to when left unattended and would benefit from continued house and crate training. animal.description: If you're someone who likes running, outdoor adventures, and LOTS of cuddles, Balthazar is the pup for you! Balthazar, aka Zar, is the ultimate package. He's athletic, he's kind, and he's so well-mannered. Zar is a total sweetheart who knows no strangers, and is always excited to meet new people and greet them with wiggles and kisses. At the end of the day though, he's ultra-loyal and wants nothing more than love and attention from his person. He expresses his love with kisses and snuggles - he totally thinks he's a lap dog, and will always seize the opportunity to get close to you. When it comes to furry friends, Zar does best with active dogs who can play and romp around with him. We haven't observed him around older, more laid back dogs before. His foster mom is working with him on refining his playtime manners - sometimes he doesn't get the hint when other dogs are annoyed with him, and needs to be corrected now and again. We also haven't observed him with cats in a home, but he frequently interacts with strays near his foster home and has shown no aggression towards them. As mentioned before, Zar loves adventures and exploring outside. His favorite activity is hiking, where he can sniff and run around to his heart's content. He's also a fabulous running companion, and would love to join you on walks too! Even though he lives for his outside activities, this curious boy is also perfectly content just hanging at home with his person. He also loves toys and can entertain himself with them if he can't talk you into a game of chase or tug of war. Zar is very well behaved in his foster home, and knows all the basic commands and even some crate training too! His foster mom is currently working with him on separation anxiety training. Separation anxiety is relatively common in shelter dogs and can be treated with some basic training and stable routines. When his person leaves the house he cries out a bit, but really, he just has FOMO. Once his person leaves though, he calms himself down pretty quickly and will go back to chewing on a bone, cuddling up in his bed, or lounging by a window to watch the world go by. He can be left alone at the house with no issues but would love it if his person works from home occasionally. Don't pass up the opportunity to meet Zar, he has so much love to give his perfect family and he can't wait to cover them in kisses and do zoomies with you!

animal.description: It's no coincidence that Taffy is named after candy...this girl is SO sweet! Taffy has an endearing curiosity and is eager to learn that the world can be full of wonderful things like tasty snacks, cozy beds, and people who adore her. Taffy came to us as a stray so her history is a mystery but we suspect that this girl would absolutely blossom with a loving, kind family. She can be a little shy at first, but once she feels comfortable, she's so happy to engage and connect. She would benefit from positive reinforcement training to help her build her confidence and learn new skills. While Taffy takes some time to feel at ease with new people, she absolutely lights up when she meets new dogs! She loves to play and would benefit from sharing her home with a social, friendly dog or by having the opportunity to have doggy playdates with her canine pals. Taffy walks beautifully on a leash and we suspect, that as you build her trust, she would make a wonderful sidekick no matter where adventure takes you.. whether it's day trips in the car or snuggles on the couch. Show this sweet girl what the good life is all about and she's sure to be your new best friend.

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete your application.**  
Herbie is a 2 year old Husky or Husky mix male that is red and white with a medium dense coat, he is 21 inches tall and we would guess 60ish pounds.
Herbie showed up at a home in early January and has stayed, he will play with the male scotty dog that lives there and has had no reaction to the neighbors cat or dogs but he is fascinated by the quail in the bramble bushes...Herbie has a lot of energy and will enjoy going for walks, he will pull since he has not had training so he will do best with a family or people who have time to spend training and taking him on adventures. From the person who is caring for Herbie: he is a love bug and is adventurous and will howl when she leaves for work. Herbie is currently living outdoors so we are not sure if he is house trained. Please apply at yvpr.org/adoptions to meet Herbie


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description:
Diamond is a sweet senior girl in need of a person, or family, who would like to take short walks, play tug with her, and cuddle during nap time. Don’t let her age fool you! Diamond maybe 13 years old, but she still has a lot of life to live! She just had her senior check up, and passed all her tests with flying colors. Diamond received a clean bill of health, and is ready to meet her furever people.  

Diamond was recently returned to us due to no fault of her own. She lived with her family for 12 years, but due to circumstances out of Diamonds control, that environment was no longer suitable for her to live her best life. 

Diamond loves to go for short, leisurely walks, where she can take her time and sniff until her hearts content. She loves to play tug of war with her favorite toys, chew her bones, and cuddle up on the couch for a good long nap.  Diamond is a happy girl, wagging her tail often, and enjoys getting massages from her person. I mean, who doesn’t enjoy a nice massage?! 

Due to a previous injury in her leg, Diamond does have some arthritis in her back leg, but don’t worry, she doesn’t let it stop her. She still gets around pretty well! 

Diamond does enjoy an easier going home and having the devotion of her people, so a home without younger kids would be best.
Diamond is currently being fostered in a home with a cat, but they are separated from each other.  A home where Diamond can be separated from cats, or a home without cats, would be best.

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Chico is a petite ~2 year old chihuahua mix who was rescued from southern CA. He will be arriving with us Sunday, December 6th. More info to come once he arrives and gets settled in!

Foster Update: Chico has quite a special story to share! He was originally rescued in CA after his previous family had to surrender him as he could no longer care for him. When Chico arrived in our rescue, it was clear he was in need of some major TLC. He was dehydrated, underweight, and skin was in rough shape - missing patches of fur throughout and his skin was red and irritated. He has had a wonderful, committed foster family to help heal him back to health and he is doing (and feeling) so much better! Chico has been on a high-protein, raw diet. His new diet has helped his itchy skin, and his fur is slowing growing back :) Chico will require a forever home committed to continuing his current diet so he can continue to feel his best self.

Chico is currently in a foster home with two other chihuahuas and two cats, and he gets along well with all of them. He has been great around his dog buddies, but would also likely do well as an only dog so he can take over the center of attention :) His temperament inside his foster home has been sweet, fun, and snuggly. He loves a cozy blanket to curl up to, and greets his fosters will a wagging tail. Chico does well in his crate, and his foster family has been working with him on his leash manners. He has been a bit insecure around other dogs on leash, which has resulted in some reactivity. Strong leadership and focus on leash manners has helped him greatly improve in this area. Chico is looking for a committed family comfortable and willing to continue to work on his leash manners.

Chico has been such a fun, loving, and wonderful little dude. He is food-motivated, smart, and eager to please. We know he is going to make one special family very happy!

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in California and will be available for adoption in Seattle, once evaluated in a loving foster home in the greater Seattle area.

animal.description:
Arthur is an adorable, approximately 9 mon old Terrier mix. He has such a sweet bubbly personality and seems to like all dogs that he meets. Arthur weighs approximately 35 lbs and would be great in any type of home setting. He walks reasonably well on a leash, loves to play and craves human affection. He was found as a stray dog and we believe that he was struck by humans. He does shy away from fast movements and often cowers when approached too quickly. He has never shown any sign of aggression, and we firmly believe he will easily overcome any prior abuse. Arthur has been tested with kids ages 10 years and 13 years old. He is very sweet and gentle, so he would likely do very well with any dog savvy child. He is short and stocky with the classic Basset legs. He would love to be a walking/hiking partner. Due to his breed we will not consider rentals.

He will be ready to transport after 2/9 to New England

Adoption fees details: 
Puppies - Adults $ 550, Seniors $375. These adoption rates include transport from Alexandria, Louisiana to designated New England adopter pick up locations and NE foster homes using either Rescue Road Trips, Pets LLC or CAFA Transport. If you do a search you will see that this is a very reasonable adoption fee and comparable to other rescues. Adoption fee breakdown:Adoption Fee:   $  365.00Transportation Fee:  $ 185.00MA and NH only--Quarantine fee if applicable:  $125.00

Medical details:
All our dogs are altered (spayed or neutered), DHLPP, rabies, Bordetella, Heartworm tested with negative test results, microchipped, treated for parasites and on monthly heartworm and flea and tick prevention. A health certificate is issued by a licensed Louisiana veterinarian.

Adoption details:  
In some instances, a meet and greet is not possible before adoption unless we have a foster home in New England available. Available for a Meeting confirms the dog is in a NE Foster home and available for a meeting in the city state provided.  Most times our dogs get adopted before a foster home becomes available - and if so, they go straight to adopters home. Foster parents talk to adopters and feel confident that this will be a match before our dogs are transported up. Also if by some chance it is not a match we have a safety net in place as we ask that adopters to let us know that it is not a match and we direct you to take the dog to a foster home or boarding kennel once that is arranged. If necessary, we will ask you to foster the dog until a foster home can be arranged. 
Transport details:Rescue Road Trips (rescueroadtrips.com), Pets LLC (petsllc.net) or CAFA Transport will deliver our precious pups on commercial rescue animal transport to designated locations.  The fee is 185.00 which IS INCLUDED in your adoption fee already.**Rescue Road Trips, was featured on The Today Show - view it at http://www.today.com/video/today/55034556#55034556

MA and NH RESIDENTS:
If you are a Massachusetts or New Hampshire residence, an additional fee of $125.00 will apply due to State quarantine fee requirements. If the dog is in a foster home in MA or NH, this fee will be added in the adoption fee regardless of where the adopters home is located making the total adoption fee $675.00 for puppies and adults $500.00 for Seniors, otherwise the full adoption fee for all other states is $550.00 for puppies and adults and $375.00 for seniors. This includes a 48 quarantine, recheck by a MA licensed veterinarian, and issued a MA health certificate.

Visit all our available dogs at www.cenlaallianceforanimals.comWe update and add dogs frequently.

We hope to help make a difference in a rescue dogs life into loving responsible homes.

animal.description:
SAVANNAH is 7 years old and weighs 10 pounds. CHLOE is 7 years old and weighs 10 pounds.

First off - we just want to state that we will each speak for ourselves, despite being presented as a bonded pair, which we are. We are very co-dependent on each other for mutual happiness and company; however, we know ourselves best and thus, will speak separately. See, we are independent littles cusses too.
My current human likes to call me Savannah Banana, although I find that Queen Savannah is infinitely more suitable. She is right that I am an emotionally in-tune kind of gal; however, I can be a bit more select in my choice of company than Chloe. That girl has no boundaries! But I will let her speak for herself. Once I make the decision to love you, there is no turning back for me. I am a love bug. I love dogs, I love cats, I love toys and I love snuggling under the  blanket in bed. My human also has a rather tasteless nickname for me calling me "roadkill" just because I sleep with my legs straight up in the air. I call it adorable myself. 

Take me on walks and I will love you forever, but I can be rather an escape artist if I'm feeling frisky. I can scale fences. I may be small, but I am fierce! Food is the thing I love best so please safeguard your trash can, unless you want to put me on Most Wanted Canines. Okay, okay, I'll let Chloe have a bark or two now.

Well, it's about time I got some air time. I am Chloe and thank heavens I have no silly nicknames, but you can call me Princess since Queen is already taken by my comrade-in-arms. Princess suits me since I have been accused of being a bit of a baby at times. I mean, just because I cry to be picked up even when I'm on the bed snuggling - what's wrong with that, I say? And yes, I do tend to be less picky than Ms. S. Banana about relationships and get along immediately with new people. Some would say that's laid back and others we don't care what they say - less emotionally mature - baa humbug. Always wondered what an actual humbug looked like anyways. My favorite trick, and always a crowd-pleaser, is being able to leave a line of pee and poop while my back legs are up in the air. You'll just have to imagine that for now.

I admit we both suffer from a bit of separation anxiety initially, given our past, I'd say that's excusable. We have been known to shred dog beds and blankets if left  alone for too long. Or, we mark places if something weird is left on the ground. I'm sure we will get over this once we know we are yours for keeps. 

So please, someone keep us! You'll just love us!




 
They both struggle with marking inside if something is on the ground or if they are left. I think they would truly benefit from being the only dogs in a home so that they can really establish themselves and not have any competition.. They both need dentals done and have bumps in their nipples. In the first stages of their rescue they were putting holes in and shredding grey blankets or dog beds- They really need someone home with them at all times, their anxiety and fear of being abandoned will take time..
They are very co-dependant and should not be separated. When I first got them their ears were all cut up and soaking wet from them chewing on each others ears. These girls have had a rough past and deserve the best.

Hello - This is Savannah barking at ya: I am a real princess - truly. Wait until you see me in person, or is that in dog? Hmmmm. 
 
INTERESTED in SAVANNAH AND CHLOE? The first step is to fill out our online Adoption Application (address link below)

NOTE: All of our dogs live in foster homes so it is not possible to setup a meet and greet prior to submitting an adoption application. Filling out an application doesn't obligate you to adopt, but it does save your place in line if there are multiple people interested.
 
ADOPTION APPLICATION (Type or cut & paste the below website address into your browser): http://www.sdroregon.com/adoption-application.htm
 
If our Adoption Coordinator determines you are a good match they will contact you. This is a great opportunity for you to find out more about SAVANNAH AND CHLOE and decide if you would like to setup a meet and greet.  
 
ADOPTION FEE is $150, and there’s a 10% Discount for Senior Citizens and Veterans.
 
Learn more about the ADOPTION PROCESS here (Type or cut & paste the below website address into your browser): http://www.sdroregon.com/adoption-process.htm

animal.description:
Hal is a feisty approximately 1.5-2 year old male Catahoula Curr mix. Hal was found as a starving stray dog. He had to be nursed back to health by the kind women who found him. She requested help from CAFA to get him vetted and placed into a forever home. Hal seems to be ok with most dogs, but we would recommend that he be dog tested with any future canine companions. He may not do well with dominant males. Hal loves to run, play and really enjoys his human love time. He has had limited exposure to kids, but we believe that he should do well with dog savvy kids ages 9 and up. Hal has a great athletic build for hiking, walking and possibly running. He has been treated for heart worm disease, and is now ready to find his forever home. Hal currently weighs 47 pounds. 

Adoption fees details: 
Puppies - Adults $ 550, Seniors $375. These adoption rates include transport from Alexandria, Louisiana to designated New England adopter pick up locations and NE foster homes using either Rescue Road Trips, Pets LLC or CAFA Transport. If you do a search you will see that this is a very reasonable adoption fee and comparable to other rescues. Adoption fee breakdown:Adoption Fee:   $  365.00Transportation Fee:  $ 185.00MA and NH only--Quarantine fee if applicable:  $125.00

Medical details:
All our dogs are altered (spayed or neutered), DHLPP, rabies, Bordetella, Heartworm tested with negative test results, microchipped, treated for parasites and on monthly heartworm and flea and tick prevention. A health certificate is issued by a licensed Louisiana veterinarian.

Adoption details:  
In some instances, a meet and greet is not possible before adoption unless we have a foster home in New England available. Available for a Meeting confirms the dog is in a NE Foster home and available for a meeting in the city state provided.  Most times our dogs get adopted before a foster home becomes available - and if so, they go straight to adopters home. Foster parents talk to adopters and feel confident that this will be a match before our dogs are transported up. Also if by some chance it is not a match we have a safety net in place as we ask that adopters to let us know that it is not a match and we direct you to take the dog to a foster home or boarding kennel once that is arranged. If necessary, we will ask you to foster the dog until a foster home can be arranged. 
Transport details:Rescue Road Trips (rescueroadtrips.com), Pets LLC (petsllc.net) or CAFA Transport will deliver our precious pups on commercial rescue animal transport to designated locations.  The fee is 185.00 which IS INCLUDED in your adoption fee already.**Rescue Road Trips, was featured on The Today Show - view it at http://www.today.com/video/today/55034556#55034556

MA and NH RESIDENTS:
If you are a Massachusetts or New Hampshire residence, an additional fee of $125.00 will apply due to State quarantine fee requirements. If the dog is in a foster home in MA or NH, this fee will be added in the adoption fee regardless of where the adopters home is located making the total adoption fee $675.00 for puppies and adults $500.00 for Seniors, otherwise the full adoption fee for all other states is $550.00 for puppies and adults and $375.00 for seniors. This includes a 48 quarantine, recheck by a MA licensed veterinarian, and issued a MA health certificate.

Visit all our available dogs at www.cenlaallianceforanimals.comWe update and add dogs frequently.

We hope to help make a difference in a rescue dogs life into loving responsible homes.

Located in Boise, Idaho.

Meet Milo! He is a 1 year old, 50 lb male, Australian Shepherd Cattle Dog looking to find his forever home! Milo is a high-energy, smart boy who will do anything for a treat. Milo currently lives in a downtown apartment with two other roommates and two other dogs. He is playful with the dogs at home but has shown protectiveness, barking and growling towards other dogs that he sees outside. Milo has been going to training since he was 6 months old and started group dog training in October! He is loved at Doggy Daycare once he is away from his mom but when I am with him he is protective towards unknown people and dogs. 
Milo's perfect home would be a place that is committed to his training and wants to expand on what he has learned. He should be  either the only dog or living with another dog who has the same training expectations and similar size to him. He is extremely on-guard and reactive while on walks but through training has developed healthy habits that must be kept up. He has not been around children or cats and I will not feel comfortable rehoming him to this living situation.                     
Milo is crate trained, potty-trained, knows "mat" as his place command, sit, lay, stay, and is working on heel. He would be an excellent candidate for scent work. I know there is a home for Milo that has more experience, time, and resources to provide for him.

Milo is neutered and fully vaccinated and has no health problems. He is located in Boise, Idaho!

animal.description: ***We urgently need a foster home for this beautiful girl.*** Reagan is not happy in the main foster home. She has to stay in a crate a lot because she doesnt do well with the dogs here. Unfortunately she is destroying her crates and we are very afraid shes going to hurt herself. If we dont find a foster home for her soon we are going to have to spend a lot of money to buy her a special crate that she cant destroy or hurt herself in. This is money that could be used for vet care and other important expenses. Reagan is truly a wonderful, loving girl. She is just not happy living with other dogs and being crated. During her playtime, she loves going for walks and cuddling. Please help us find her a foster home. You can see from looking at Reagan that she has had an incredibly rough life. She has scars on her face and legs, she was bred likely multiple times, and she has tumors all over her body (we now believe they are benign). Her body looks aged beyond its actual years. Despite the neglect and abuse Reagan endured, her love for people has not wavered. She truly just wants to be around people and know how it feels to be loved by a family. Reagan is spayed, up to date on vaccinations, flea treated, wormed, heartworm positive (currently being treated), lymes negative, and microchipped. She is currently on Benedryl and needs to remain on it as it helps inhibit the growth of masses. She is dog selective but seems to be ok with cats. She is very uncomfortable in the main foster home with all the other dogs. Please help us find a foster family for Reagan. If you are interested please complete an application. **Applications will not be screened if they do not meet adoption requirements. **

My name is Digger. I am in the market for a new home because my moms work schedule (she takes care of sick people) has changed a lot and I was home by myself all the time. I am crate trained but I hate it and do my best to get out. I have a bit of anxiety in new situations so it may take me a few days to settle in. I love my people, car rides and going for walks. I would love to have a dog sibling in my new home that likes to play but isn't all high strung like some young dogs can be. Are you looking for a dog like me??

I am crate trained, I sleep in one at night. I am still working on potty training but foster Mom says I’m doing really good. I’m still learning not to bite when I play, foster Mom says my puppy teeth are sharp. I have never been around cats but I love kids.

I can also whip up the best meringue you’ve ever had!

-I need to stay local to the Springfield, Mo area so I can finish my vetting or wait until my vetting is finished to go out of the area.

animal.description:
Well, how do you do folks?  Popcorn is my name and I am very eager to meet you.  I am a 3 1/2 year old male poodle mix from Shanghai, weighing a compact 18lb and 16 inches tall.

My owner dumped me outside of a shelter in Shanghai. When I first arrived there I developed a bad habit of biting my own tail because of anxiety.

I had found a home in Canada, but I started to attack my back foot as well as my tail, to the point where my owner couldn't leave me at home alone and had to bring me to work. So, she's made the painful decision to rehome me, in hopes that someone will find me that can be home all the time to monitor me. She thinks it's because of either pain, or a history of being tied up by my leg back in Shanghai. I will growl and snap at anyone who tries to touch my back end or stop me during one of my tail/leg attacks.

I had surgery done once I arrived to Canada to fix a luxating patella, and also had to get some of my teeth removed. The surgery definitely helped with some of the pain in my leg. I'm on a few different medications right now to try to help more.

A few reasons why you should bring me home: once I am close to you, I am super cuddly! I can cuddle with you all day on the couch. I also absolutely love going for walks and being outside, and I love to run around and play with other dogs as long as they aren't too energetic for me. I'm also housetrained, and am great in the car.

I'm also great around kids, as long as they respect my boundaries and are gentle with me. Cats, not so much. I want to chase them if they interact with me.

I like practically anyone as long as they are gentle with me, but if you have a super deep voice, it might frighten me a bit. I also don't like to be picked up because I'm so conscious of my back end and tail. 

I have quite a bit of separation anxiety, so a household where someone can be home most of the time would be ideal for me. A quiet house would do me good too, since I'm not great with people coming to the door. I'm okay with people once they are inside and I know that I can trust them, especially if they leave me be. I just like to be left alone most of the time.

My current owner says I'm the sweetest little guy. So what do you say, do you want to bring me home?

I am neutered, vaccinated and microchipped and my adoption fee is $650 CAD + applicable taxes.

 

Disclaimer: It is important for all applicants to visit our website,  http://www.lovedatlastdogrescue.ca/adopting/  and to read about Loved at Last Dog Rescue. 

 

Information included in the profile is provided to us from the international rescuer or local fosters. LALDR does not have access to overseas dogs and cannot always verify the accuracy of the descriptions. Remember, every dog is an individual and can act differently in different situations based on the person leading him and the environment. The age and breed of a dog is almost always an educated guess and at no time do we promise or guarantee the age or breed of a dog. 

 

Normally, we will not approve adoptions to homes with children under 12 years of age. More information can be found on our website.

animal.description:
Blossom is looking for an active home with a yard and another playful med/large dog.  She is about 35lbs and thought to be around 3yrs old.  She shows some herding tendencies with people (and other dogs), so would do best in a home with kids over 12. Blossom came from Mexico with a non contagious skin condition so it still growing in fur, but she is ready to start her search for the perfect home. 

Here is what her fostermom has to say about this special girl:

Blossom is the puppy playmate of the year. Every dog who meets with her vies for her playtime, often surrounding her and trying to get her attention first. She is currently in love with her young foster brother and would like to have another playful dog to live with. They wrestle throughout the day and often nap on top of each other. When she isn’t romping with other dogs she likes fetching balls, car rides, and squeaky toys. She is house trained, dog door trained, and crate trained. Blossom also adores “her people” as well. She takes a while to be affectionate with new humans but when she realizes they are part of her pack she is loyal and extremely loving. She wants to protect her pack and will alarm bark for every person or car that drops by. Due to her barking she will need to go to a quiet home or big yard where the neighbors will not find that bothersome. Even though Blossom began her with a very ruff start on the streets of Tijuana she remains happy and healthy. Her coat is still growing back in, and although she will likely fill out more, her coat remains thick enough for her to enjoy the snow up in Truckee at her foster home. Blossom gets the “zoomies” in the snow and runs joyous laps on fresh powder days. She is an awesome powder hound but would be happy anywhere as long as she has a family to call her own.

Please email right away if you would like to learn more about this dog......and visit our website www.siarescuers.org to learn more about our rescue group.   Adoption fees range from $200-$400 for dogs.  THE DOGS SHOWN ON THE SITE ARE IN FOSTERCARE - WE DO NOT HAVE A SHELTER TO VISIT.  EMAIL is the best way to reach us.We are a volunteer run, very small organization - so please be patient when waiting for a response, but feel free to check back in if you haven't heard from us in a day or so - thank you so much for considering a rescued pooch!

You can also email us at adoptions@lostourhome.org.

Do not fill out the application on this site, this is a courtesy post and the dog is not with Underdog Rescue

PLEASE NOTE: This dog is courtesy posted for another individual or Rescue. Different policies and fees may apply.

MEET RORY!

Rory is approx 6 years old. Looking for her forever home!!

You will find me waiting pretty and proper with my favorite little teddy bear in my mouth. It's the only thing I have with me still from my old life and it brings me comfort. I love my toys and I sure love to show them off, I really don't think it's too much to ask for a family to spoil me with lots of toys (squeaky ones) and affection because I am a silly pup stuck in a big girl body!!

I'd love to be your one and only pet, I'm not the best at sharing the spotlight. This new age world has some crazy things that really scare me, like TVs, vacuums, and dishwashers. But you can't blame me, I'm not even from this century! I'm a simple dog who needs a slow introduction to these fast-changing times! I love my kennel because it helps me feel safe at night, and I am very much potty trained in a home. I get anxious when left alone, but that's just because I have a love for people that LOVE ME.

If you are looking to open your heart to once in a LIFETIME pet who can share the secrets of the past with you, while we walk hand in paw into the future together, please take the time to apply to meet me! I can't wait for the op-paw-tunity to meet you!

All dog adoptions include the following:

--Spay/neuter surgery

--All current vaccinations

--Microchip with free chip registration

--Free wellness exam through VCA Animal Hospitals

--Access to our Behavior Helpline for the lifetime of the pet

animal.description:
?? Everyone, please meet BARNEY!!! ??

*** PLEASE SHARE, if willing ***

? Barney was rescued by Animal Rescue Relay from the shelter in Fresno, CA, where he was listed as a stray. 

? Barney is a chihuahua mix and probably only weighs about 7-8 lbs. Barney came to the rescue very emaciated and scared. Trying to put some meat on his bones...

? Barney is neutered and will be all up to date on shots! I’m guessing Barney is around 10 years old. Barney is very mobile but appears walk slowly as his hind legs look feeble.

? Barney’s past is completely unknown, but it seems obvious that we was most like neglected and abused, Barney takes while to warm up. Barney likes to stay in ‘the mix’ and follow you around, but at this point he prefers not to be let or touched unless he initiates it first. 

? Barney has no teeth so he needs some soft food as an option but he had been seen gumming small bites dry dog food.

? Barney is good around my other dogs, large and small, as long as they don’t invade his space.  Barney will correct other dogs appropriately with a low growl. Barney is not aggressive.

? Barney us a special little old man, and will need to go to a home that is quiet, without small children and preferably with experience with abused dogs. Barney loves nothing more than cuddling on your lap or the bed, but only when he chooses it.

? Barney is very intelligent and observant.

? Barney is extra gentle with my blind fister babies and seems to enjoy looking after LuLu, as he can be seen gently guarding her as she sleeps quite often. 

? If you’d like to meet Barney, please contact me, Anderson Rose, in a PM.

? Applications can be completed via:

https://animalrescuerelay.org/adoption-application/

? Adopting seniors, or dogs with disabilities takes very special homes... please consider the rewards of taking in a soul that other threw away carelessly. 

Heidi Neilson, Kelly Pettit-Lopez, Vanessa Jennings

animal.description:
1. PLEASE NOTE: Breed mix info is the best guess of Bark Bark Wag and our vets. There is no way to know for certain what any dog's breed mix is without a DNA test; and most mixed-breed dogs may have 3, 4, 5 different breeds in their mix!

2. MUST READ --THE FIRST STEP: Go to www.barkbarkwag.org and click on "Let's Get Started!" to learn about our easy 3-step adoption process & apply to adopt! ANSWERS TO MOST QUESTIONS CAN BE FOUND HERE! We are all volunteers with limited time to respond to emails; if your question involves something NOT addressed at "Let's Get Started!", we will respond ASAP!

*WE NEED AN ADOPTION APPLICATION TO START THE PROCESS*

SUPER SNUGGLER ALERT!  
Ranger is a handsome, unique young man who is looking for some new faces to kiss with his crazy tongue!  He's 18 months old, a great/compact size at 35#, and believed to be a mix of Dachshund and American Staffordshire Terrier (we aren't kidding)!  He is a very loving, loyal, and wonderful companion to his person/people. He adores climbing into your lap, burrowing under the covers with you, or fitting himself in just about anywhere he can to give you some love!  

If you're working at home, he's happy to lay by your feet or curl up on the couch chewing a bone until you're through. If you need a movie-watching buddy or a napping partner to keep you warm, Ranger's your guy! Up for an adventure? Ranger loves to see and do new things, and enjoys exploring trails on a hike, or going for walks down a quiet road!  Any activity you can dream up, Ranger is willing, ready, and happy to join in.  He is super friendly and sociable, and greets new people with excitement and happy wags!  Due to his exuberant greetings, we are recommending an adult family for Ranger, preferably without other animals so he can get the lion's share of affection!  He is extremely smart and easy to teach (especially with the promise of a treat, which he takes oh-so-gently!). If he's sitting in your 'spot' on the couch, just point to where you'd like him to be -- he will move there so you can sit down, then this little lover will smoosh in close to you.  

He's house-trained, and will wait by the door to ask to go outside.  He knows 'sit', 'stay', and is quick to pick up on cues.  Ranger would love a family who wants to teach him tricks, do different types of activities, and keep his mind engaged.  His ideal family will give him the opportunity to experience new things and to use all his senses. He loves to sniff and investigate his world, and a forever home with some fields and woods would make his heart happy!  Ranger does not enjoy a crate--he is happiest on the couch or a dog bed, and he'd love a family who is home more often than not. Ranger is looking for an adult person or adult family he can give allllll his love to, and who will make him their best friend!

animal.description:
Frankie is a 2 year old, White Shepherd mix that was surrendered to the rescue for having a pinched nerve. After several weeks of laser therapy and rest, he is now symptom free. Now that Frankie is feeling his best, he is ready to start the search for his FURever family. 

Characteristic of his breed description, Frankie is loyal and loving. He is affectionate towards people and loves the company of other dogs. Frankie enjoys running outside and going for long walks. He is excellent on a leash and is very responsive to commands. As with any dog, Frankie would benefit from a structured daily routine and continued training once he settles into his new home.

In order to be considered as a potential adopter, we will need you to complete our online application at www.arrus.org. Should we choose to move forward with your family, you will be notified via email within the week. Due to the large volume of applications received, we are no longer able to respond to each and every applicant. We apologize in advance for the inconvenience and appreciate your understanding. 

Additional information and/or medical records for this rescue pet are available and will be reviewed in person should we choose to move forward in scheduling a meet n’ greet. In the meantime, please feel free to follow us on follow us on Instagram (animal_rescue_r_us) and visit our Facebook page at www.facebook.com/arrusadopt for more pictures and posts from his/her foster family. 

HELP US, HELP THEM! Animal Rescue R Us is a 501(c)(3) non-profit organization. We do not receive county, state or federal funding and rely solely on donations. These donations help offset the cost of routine veterinary care, medical expenses, and other necessities while the rescue animal is in our  care. To make a secure donation, please visit www.arrus.org/donate . Alternatively, you may visit our Amazon Wishlist (http://www.amazon.com/registry/wishlist/C36VRV500R85) for a current list of needed supplies! All donations are tax-deductible and all are greatly appreciated. Thank you for your support!

animal.description:
Meet Bo!

12-year-old Bo was brought to the San Diego Humane Society after his owners passed away. He had a full veterinary work-up at SDHS and is quite the healthy senior gentleman! He needs dental surgery to remove a few fractured teeth and clean the others. Bo also has cyst on his eyelid that is in a good location for removal, likely at the same time as his dental. Otherwise, his bloodwork, urinalysis, and ultrasound came back normal.

A few hours after arriving on January 27th, Bo was scooped up for a two-week Frosted Fling! We received this great update from Bo's Fling Mom: "Bo is such a fun and loving boy! He loves toys and can entertain himself with a ball for quite some time, but he also LOVES a good game of fetch and will keep nudging at the ball for you to play with him if you stop. He has a great appetite and is super food motivated and will sit almost instantly if he thinks he might get a treat. He knows sit, down, and seems to know his name and have some recall. He loves all the people he's met and will throw his whole body at you for pets. He walks great on a leash and has a good pace - I think he would make a great hiking/adventure buddy. He definitely acts younger than 12 years old. He seems like he still has so much life left to live, and he has so much love to give to a lucky family."

Be sure to watch the video of Bo playing fetch and showing off the commands he knows!

Visit us at Open House: Saturdays & Sundays, 10 am - 1 pm

Learn more about our programs at www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/family. No adoption fees, and we help with medical costs!

Apply to become a family: www.frostedfacesfoundation.org/apply

Questions: adopt@frostedfacesfoundation.org

animal.description:
Red Bean a super sweet and calm little guy.  He is a bit nervous with people and dogs at first, but warms up with patience.  He was rescued after being dumped in a remote area with several other dogs.  He deserves to know the love of a forever home.

You can complete an adoption application on our website at:  
     www.onceuponatailrescue.com
or
     Scroll down on this page & click "More About Us", & then click "Adoption            Application" underneath our bright Pink logo. 

If you want to meet a pup in person, Once Upon a Tail Rescue does adoption events at PetSmart in Covington, LA on most Saturdays with many of our adoptable dogs there. 

Don't forget to complete your application ahead of time, so you don't miss out on the pup you've connected with.  If pre-approved, you have first priority & can usually take home your new best friend the same day!  

*Please note that there is no obligation to adopt by completing an application.*

**All dogs are required to have complete vet services, including shots, rabies, spay/neuter and microchip, which are included in the Adoption Fee. Some dogs may still require completion of these services due to current age, size, breed and/or health. All vet services must be done at the vet clinic used by Once Upon a Tail Rescue.

animal.description:
Carmen just arrived and is looking for a foster home without other pets, or where she can be kept separate. 

She is 4- 5 years old and weighs in at about 26  lbs.  Carmen is heart-worm positive and has started medication regiment. 

The heart worm treatment itself will take place mid March and we would like to see her undergo the treatment in a foster home in Calvert County or nearby if possible.   Carmen is a love and excellent companion. She appears to be house-trained and kennels up well. She is not a huge barker.

To apply for Carmen to foster her through treatment (this is a crate rest and leash out only obligation for about 2 months)  you should fill our our foster application at www.puppypawsrescue.org... OR if you want to foster Carmen with the option to adopt, fill out our adoption agreement.. same location.

--------------------------------------------------------------------
After heartworm treatment and crate rest, dogs can be expected to test positive for up to 6 months after.

If interested in adopting please fill out our no obligation online application at www.puppypawsrescue.org

Note: Our rescue requires that all adopter's current and prior animals are up-to-date on vaccinations (DHLPP & Rabies) and preventatives (heartworm and flea and tick), unless there is a medical reason not allowing it. All animals in your household should be spayed or neutered unless medically indicated that they should not be or are currently still too young.

animal.description: Hi I'm Abby. People might describe me as bashful or maybe a little sensitive to my surroundings. This just means you'll be the apple of my eye and my source of safety and security. I'm looking for a person that will understand me and help me gain confidence at my own pace. I would appreciate a quiet, low-traffic home, as a busy household may be overwhelming for me. I need a home where any children are at least in their teens. Because I get a tad nervous with noises and meeting new people, I'm probably not cut out for apartment-living. I'm a dog that needs to be the star of the show. This means that I need a home where I'm the only dog so your attention will solely be on me for your canine companionship. I need to meet all family members in the home to make sure it's a perfect match. Abby will be shown by appointment only. If you are interested in learning more about this animal, please fill out an application by clicking here . Be sure to include Abby 1370120 when filling out the survey. animal.description: This sweet girl was abandoned by her owners then ran around town looking for food until she got pregnant. Then someone finally put a plea on social media for rescue to help because by then she had lost trust in people. Thankfully after sitting in an old dark crowded barn for 20 hours, our volunteer was able to rescue her and her 5 babies. The babies have been adopted and our sweet but shy Lu is ready for a nice quiet home with a family who will give her the time and space she needs to form a bond. If you are interested in this lady please visit funnyfarmrescueranch.org to find the adoption application and to read all about the adoption process.

"Why yes, as a matter of fact I DO know I'm super cute!" SPROUT is an absolutely adorable chihuahua mix boy looking for a furever home. He loves people, and loves to be loved on. We think he'd be okay with another small dog, or fine on his own. Bigger dogs make him nervous. Sprout is 2 years old and fully grown at 14 lbs. He's fine on a leash and we think he'd be okay in an apartment or condo. Some of Sprout's coat was dyed pink at some point, and his nails had been painted pink as well. Whoever styled him did not care enough to love him furever, because he ended up terrified in a rural shelter. We've promised Sprout we'll find him a home where he will be loved for the rest of his life. If you'd like to meet adorable Sprout, please fill out a foster-to-adopt application at
dreamhouserescue.org.

All of our fully-vetted adoptable dogs go to prospective homes for a one-week trial foster-to-adopt period to make sure the dog and home are the right fit before an adoption is finalized. We only adopt dogs into homes where all current pets are spayed/neutered and current on vaccines and heartworm and flea and tick prevention. We do check veterinary references to make sure adopters are compliant with standard veterinary care.

animal.description:
Meet Heaven & Angel
-Female
-Approximately 1.5 years old
-Lab/Pinscher MIX

Heaven & Angel came to us with nothing more than skin and bones after being dumped on someone's driveway. They survived for each other. The way they love each other is just unexplainable. They have been through the worst together and because of this, they will experience the best together. Heaven & Angel ARE A BONDED PAIR.

Heaven (IN PINK) is:
-Playful
-Loving
-Submissive
-Nervous/Anxious
-Friendly
-Crate trained

Angel (IN BLUE) is:
-Energetic
-Loving
-Dominant
-Nervous/Anxious
-Sweet/Kind
-Crate trained

Both ladies are AMAZING with other dogs and do well with children. They tend to play bite and jump so we do suggest supervision if children are under 10 years of age. They absolutely LOVE to play with other dogs as they never knew what fun was until they joined our family! 
They are SO loving and will love you very much. Although Angel is more the attention seeker, Heaven will never turn down some pets! Heaven is more of the mellow one where she won't bother you for things or chase other dogs. She gives you your time and will accept any love sent her way. These two girls COMPLETE EACHOTHER in every way. 

They would do best with:
-An ACTIVE family
-Home with FENCED IN YARD
-Home with LOTS OF ACCESS TO THE OUTDOORS
-Someone who has enough love for the both of them

If you believe Heaven & Angel are meant for you, please fill out an adoption application: https://form.jotform.com/93263081961156

IF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS PLEASE EMAIL INFO@MERCYFULLPROJECTS.ORG

animal.description:
This gentle Beagle was named Lady by her owner.

She's 2 years old, weights just 27 lbs. and previously lived with a toddler.
She's good with other dogs & cats as well. She was surrendered by her family. 
She's very quiet, observing all that surrounds her, this is probably why she failed as a "hunting dog".
She just wants to be a family member, she has no interest in chasing anything. 

A quiet home would be best suited for her with an understanding family.
She had already had a litter prior to coming in but was spayed on Monday, so no more puppies for Lady! and no more hunting trips, just laps, couches & beds are what we are looking for.
She walks nicely on a leash & is getting extra TLC from us to build her confidence. 

Lady is available for adoption now, if interested please apply at www.amherstanimalshelter.org/adopt

Adoption fee & vetting include: Exam, Distemper, rabies, deworm, flea protection, 3 way heart-worm test and alter.

Our hours are:
Monday - Friday 10-4, Wednesday open until 6 p.m. and Saturday 9-1.

animal.description:
COURTESY POST (Northern VA) Meet sweet George! He's a 5-year-old pup in need of a new home. He lived with the same couple since he was a puppy and used to be a trusting dog until he was attacked by 2 unknown dogs in a dog park and he became very fearful. He was attacked in his lower back, so he is particularly worried of anyone reaching for that spot. Although his family loves George dearly, his current home is going through major changes and he needs stability and not a lot of visitors. He desperately needs a home that will help him build confidence and learn to trust again. George is a wonderful, intelligent, and obedient pup. He knows his commands and is food motivated.
George's criteria for a new home include, a calm, low-traffic home, a home with adults only (or older, considerate kids, ages 15+); he is not good around small kids as he does not like sudden movements or loud noise, someone that is home most of the day, a home with a fenced yard.
George LOVES cats!!! He has had canine BFFs in the past, so he has been socialized and is fully capable of accepting certain dogs, but since he is dog-selective, a meet and greet with the resident dog is a must.
He is vaccinated, neutered, and house trained. His adoption fee is $300. If you're interested in adopting this sweet boy, please complete an adoption application at lovepawspg.org.
Note: George is not a LOVEPAWS dog. We are courtesy posting him for his family, so we will share all adoption applications with the person helping his family find him a new home and she will reach out to applicants directly.

animal.description:
Meet Nicholas and Noelle! They are 4 month old husky/pitbull mix puppies. We would love to see this brother and sister pair adopted together. They will grow to be large size dogs and will need a fenced yard. They are typical puppies. Very sweet, cuddly and playful! They will need a home where they will have plenty of room to grow, and a patient household to help them learn the do's and don't of puppyhood! If you would like to make Nicholas and Noelle a part of your family, fill out an application at www.barktownrescue.org.
Adoption Fee For Pair: $250The shelter software system requires that we choose a predominant breed or breed mix for our dogs. Visual breed identification in dogs is unreliable so for most of our dogs we are only guessing at the dog's predominant breed or breed mix. We strongly encourage you to select your new pet by looking at each dog's individual personality and pet qualities rather than relying on a breed label that is only our best guess.

Our adoption fees vary from $150 and up. All of our dogs are up to date on vaccines, heart worm preventives, and flea/tick medication, and will be spayed/neutered prior to adoption. Portions of your adoption fee also help care for the sick and injured animals that we take in. Thank you for supporting us and considering a rescue dog!
