animal.description:
Surprised we are posting Dr Cornelia Cloud, she is very near and dear to our heart. On Dec 5th, she came to us from NYC ACC as a stray. She was all matted, so recently shaved, freezing and skin and bones. We got her on a feeding schedule and got her strong enough for a spay and some lower teeth extractions.
Miss Cloud also known as Bean is 7 years old and fully vetted.
She is being fostered in Randolph MA with 7 other dogs and a cat. She can chase the cat so recommending no cats for her forever home. She exists well with other dogs but does want to be the center of attention. If not a single dog home than an experienced home with multiple small dogs a must.
She is used to being in a fenced yard or being carried. She sleeps on the bed at night and will need that accommodation moving forward.
Bean is an early riser and wants breakfast around 630AM so non morning people do not apply :) 
Dr Cornelia Cloud is an amazing pup and the family we pick will be filled with daily smiles and cuddles.
Our application can be found on our website on the available dogs page.
Thank You!

OUR ADOPTION PROCESS AND APPLICATION ARE AVAILABLE AT WWW.SOHODOGRESCUE.ORG AND OUR ADOPTION FEE IS $275.

Martin is a very happy and friendly Border Collie who is ready for his forever home.  He is 5 years old, a great weight at 45 pounds, and he has that classic black and white Border Collie coat and a full tail.  Martin is housebroken, create-trained and knows some basic obedience commands.  He rides great in the car and walks pretty well on leash.
Martin is shy when he first meets someone new, but he warms up quickly and then it is game on!  He loves to play with his foster family.  Martin is a medium energy guy who loves to play catch and will return the ball or toy and drop it in your lap every time!  He also loves to play tug of war with rope toys but he is not pushy about play – he will wait until you invite him.  Martin also loves to play with other dogs, and when not playing he loves to just hang out with his dog pals.  He really enjoys their company.  Martin stalks the resident cat.
The ideal home for Martin is friendly and loving, shared with people who are ready to welcome a great guy like Martin into their lives.  A fenced yard is important, another playful dog would be welcome, and children over the age of 12 are fine with him.  Martin would also do best with a family where someone is home during the day.  He is such a “people dog”, and the more time he can spend with friendly humans the better!  This amazing guy will add so much to his next home.  If you are “in the market for a Martin”, apply today!  Martin is fostered in West Jefferson, NC.

animal.description:
Hi!  I'm Sadie.  I was a stray in Alabama and some nice people took me in.  Sadly, they lost their home and had to move into a rental.  Well....here's where the trouble started.....The landlord would not let them keep me inside so they put me in a pen outside.  This MIGHT have been ok except that there were these things with horns (goats) running around in a pasture not 15 feet from me!  What is a bored girl to do??!?!?  I kept breaking out and chasing them. I wasn't going to hurt them.  I just loved to see them run from me.  The landlord said if they did not get rid of me he was going to shoot me.  So....here I am homeless again.  If you let me be inside with you I promise I won't chase your other pets with horns!  

COMPLETED APPLICATIONS TAKE PRECEDENCE OVER INQUIRIES! IF you are interested in adopting, the FIRST step is to complete an application! Please email for an Application or copy and paste the following URL: 

https://fs26.formsite.com/nogreaterlove/form2/index.html 

Upon receipt of your application, the rescuer and foster in AL will contact you so you can ask any specific questions you may have! If there is more than one decision maker in the home, all of them should be in agreement! 

 Adoption Donation: Unless otherwise stated in the pet's bio, our standard adoption fee is $395 which covers age appropriate vaccines (DHPP vax) and (Rabies vax if 12 weeks and older), utd on flea/tick prevention and heartworm prevention, worming, heartworm test @ age 6 months or older, microchip, fostering costs and health certificate.

Thank you for your understanding and consideration and for helping the dogs and puppies in need!

We do not adopt to anyone under the age of 21

animal.description:
Approx. DOB: 12/01/12 Approx Weight: 75 Lbs
Adoption Fee: $150 includes a 2 week trial to ensure everyone's happiness!

Are you looking for a Sweet, gentle, senior who is very handsome? Then I might just be the guy for you!!!
I am completely housebroken. I don't enjoy being crated, but I am really well behaved in the house and free roam at my foster home. I do well with other dogs I have met in foster so far, but should be fed separately as I tend to really not want other dogs around me while I munch on my food. I am a really loving guy and would be so happy just relaxing on the couch while my humans watch TV.
When I came to FKR I had happy tail.... because I was always wagging it and hitting it on all objects in my way which made it bleed on the end. I had to have my tail amputated and feel much better now. I am strong on a leash and would benefit from obedience classes and a harness. A fenced in yard is required for me please.

I have been neutered, vaccinated, heartworm tested negative, wormed and microchipped. If you are interested in adopting me, please complete the adoption application located at www.furrykidsrefuge.org/adoptadog and a dedicated volunteer will get back to you as soon as possible.
Furry Kids' Refuge is in need of good quality dog and puppy food with meat as the first ingredient. You can drop off donations at our weekly adoption events at the Lee's Summit Petco (1860 NW Chipman Road, Lee's Summit, MO), Saturdays only from Noon to 4:00 p.m. Donations are tax deductible as allowed by law.
Would you like to foster a Furry Kid? Furry Kids' Refuge will supply the food & vet care while you supply the basic house rules & love.......win-win for all!! Just visit our website http://www.furrykidsrefuge.org/category/fostering/ for more information. Thanks for your support!

animal.description:
Stu (Stuart) is looking for his forever home. 

Stu is a beautiful, affectionate, fun, and healthy 3-year-old Rottweiler, coming from a loving home.  

We want nothing more for him than to have a happy and fulfilling life and are devastated to admit that, after 3 years together, our lifestyle is not what is best for him. 

Stu loves to be around his humans and snuggle up with them.  He loves to play tug and fetch and get his excited growls going.  He also loves to eat! He currently eats a raw diet, as well as raw marrow bones and treats. Cucumber, carrots, and romaine lettuce are his favorite vegetables, but he’ll take any dog friendly snack you’re offering! 

Stu requires a predictable lifestyle, with no children. He has had a few incidents of aggression in the past, where he has bitten people on the arm or hand. It is usually related to resource guarding, and he seems uncomfortable in large crowds. An experienced, compassionate, and dedicated owner is essential for Stu to feel safe. 

Stu would do well with a single person or couple who do not frequently have children over. He is crate trained and does well in the crate during times where he needs a safe space away from the action. 

Stu’s Temperament 
•	Very sweet, snuggly, and affectionate
•	Loves to play, growls excitedly while playing 
•	Obedient 
•	Food motivated
•	Excited to see you but calms quickly, rarely jumps, if ever
•	Low prey drive 
•	Loves to be at home, on walks with his humans, or running around  

Stu’s Training 
•	Obedience 
•	Good recall
•	Crate trained
•	E-collar trained
•	Some muzzle training

Owner Suitability
•	Experienced with large breeds  
•	Able to put him in situations where he will be successful
•	Experienced in handling dogs who have shown some aggression in the past
•	Able show affection as well as set appropriate boundaries 
•	Fenced in yard or other appropriate boundaries

To apply or ask questions about Stu please contact stuart.ottawa@gmail.com

animal.description:
Morgan is a big boy weighing in at 100 pounds!  He is quite handsome and is estimated to be between the age of 1-3 years old. 

He is very connecting and craves closeness, he is just happy to be by you.  Morgan is all loose, wiggly and outgoing too, just a silly boy.  He will definitely need a fun, active home with a lot of playtime and walks though, as he has a lot of energy.  He absolutely loves toys, so he would appreciate it if his new home could maybe have a few of those!  

It would be wonderful if his new family could work on some basic obedience with him, he knows sit, but he is in need of leadership and someone to set limits.  Morgan really needs an experienced adopter, this sweet guy has just never been taught how to conduct himself properly.  He doesn't seem to realize his size and strength.  Morgan would also do best in a home where any children were at least 13 years old, he can be a bit mouthy with toys and jumpy for attention.  It wouldn't hurt if he had a little help with losing a few pandemic pounds too, which we can all understand!  

We also have exciting news to share about Morgan and 3 other dogs at our rescue. They are participating in a Teacher's Pet program in which they travel twice a week to Crossroads, an at youth risk center, and are paired with a youth. They will be working with our pups on some obedience training and giving them some much needed one on one time. What a wonderful program, we are so happy about it and thrilled for our dogs.

If you are interested in Morgan and are at least 21 years old, please fill out an application at K9stray.com and we will be in touch.

home_environment_attributes.other_animals: No cats or small critters for this boy.

animal.description:
Cereza / Female / 5 Months / 27 lbs / Street Mix / Toronto

Meet Cereza! Cereza is described by her fosters as an oversized lap dog, who loves to be as close as possible to her people! She will roll over for belly rubs every time she thinks there’s a chance for one. She loves to be a part of her pack and does best when her canine pals and humans are near. Her puppy cuteness comes out when she boops things with her nose to figure out what they are. Still very much a puppy, she is playful, loving and is excited everyday to explore the world around her!

With new people, Cereza can be timid and may chose to stay in her own space. She takes time to realize people aren’t a threat but she wants to make new friends. Once she warms up she will come over to give gentle kisses. She knows a dog lover - and warms up much quicker. Potential adopters should have realistic expectations when meeting her and building a relationship with her.

Cereza is gentle with all children, but she likes when they respect her space. She has been known to bark at come children if they move too quickly or take her things (toys). She is never aggressive but given she is just 5 months, proper socialization will be essential for her success. Her forever family will need to find ways to create positive social experiences and confidence meeting new people. Once she trusts children, she wants nothing more than to their best friend for life.

First thing in the morning, Cereza gets a potty break and then tries to go right back to sleep on the couch. She is walked every 2-3 hours and will go up to 9 hours (at night) without a break. She never marks but she will have accidents if her humans are not paying attention to her signals. She is still potty training and will need to continue in her forever home!

She is very fearful of loud noises so she needs to be safely secured at all times while outside. She is timid and stubborn on leash, but walks much better when she is part of a pack. When walking one on one, she will generally chose to do her business and their usher her humans back inside. Although she loves other dogs she may take time to warm up to them. Once she feels safe, she will happily approach and play with other dogs.
Cereza is very smart and she has already learned sit. She is currently learning paw and stay! Further obedience and trick training has been great for her confidence overall.

Cereza’s ideal home would be outside of the city, so she can learn to be more confident outside. She would love to have a fully fenced backyard to play or do her business; but its not essential if her humans are home to work with her potty schedule. She would absolutely love to have another dog to follow around and boost her confidence.

If you’re interested in adopting Cereza please apply at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/adoption-info#adoption-form

Cereza’s adoption fee is $800. To learn more about our adoption fees and the adoption process, please visit our FAQs at https://www.fetchandreleash.ca/about-us#about-faqs.

animal.description:
This little ball of fun is Mobley. He has been with PawsUp since early Dec. He came to us covered in mange and missing most of his fur, but it is really starting to fill in now!  The mange is gone (and was not of the contagious variety).  He will have a full coat soon and man is he cute.  His personality shines.  He is a happy boy with lots of love to give.  Mobley is a 5 month old MinPin mix, at best guess. 

This little guy is the best. He makes me laugh every.single.day!!  You know that friend that sees the good in everyone and wants everyone around them to be happy?  That’s Mobley!!  You know those dogs that spend more time on their back 2 legs than all 4 and you see them bopping up and down trying to see things twice as high as them?  That’s Mobley!!  
He is the happiest little guy you’ve ever seen. He’s loving, gives never ending kisses, he sits for treats, but then gets so excited, that he has to help you give him the treat with his paws. He is doing better with his potty training, but still needs positive reinforcement and lots of treats!!

Mobley sleeps all night (in our bed). He is not a fan of the crate, so he would do best in a home where his people are home a majority of the time. He loves all the dogs in his foster home and loves people, but is hesitant at first. If his foster home pups aren’t into playing, he entertains himself. He loves his toys!!  When he’s really into playing, he gets a little crazy and the gremlin in him comes out. He makes the cutest little gremlin noises!!

To be considered the first step is to apply here: https://www.pawsup4rescue.org/dog-cat-applicaiton 
We are located in Joliet Illinois and require adopters be within a 100 mile radius to adopt. If your app is picked we will be in touch by phone to set up a private meet.  If the dog is adopted we will post the adoption pic. Information on fees can be found here: https://www.pawsup4rescue.org/

animal.description:
Meet Jack. He came to us from a hoarding situation while he has made a lot of progress under our care, he is still fearful when it comes to new situations. Jack enjoys people and affection but tends to be bossy with other dogs and has an alpha personality, so we think he'd enjoy being the only dog in the home. He will require a quiet, dog savvy family without young kids and with the patience to allow him to explore new surroundings on his own time. We are estimating he is apx. 3 years old.

Thank you for showing interest in our dogs, however due to the recent influx of applications and emails we ask that you avoid sending emails asking if: a listed dog is still available, if we received your application, or if we have additional photos (we always post whatever we have). Due to the current pandemic we have been receiving a huge influx of interest and emails and appreciate your help in lessening the workload for our volunteers. 

PLEASE NOTE: If you are interested in adopting a dog or puppy, please follow the steps below and submit an application. If you have questions you must reach out to us as we do not have the capacity to individually contact all applicants. You may call 559-393-1946 between 6PM and 9PM if you have additional questions AFTER SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION. During this time we are only accepting appointments at our Kingsburg facility, so please do not apply for a dog if you are not willing to drive to us.

Our dogs may be met by appointment locally in Kingsburg. Copy and paste the link below to submit a pre-screen application for the dog of interest, or find the link on our website www.pawsitiveconnections.org. Due to the overwhelming amount of interest our dogs have been receiving during this time, we unfortunately will not be able to reach out to all applicants who apply. If you do not receive correspondence from us, it is likely a reflection of the amount of applications we received. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScGSOxbGTIIintrGXUi8H-ddLv41aA0XUbELmNi0YhUIWQHRA/viewform

Adoption fee will include spay/neuter, microchip, rabies vaccine (dependent on age), bordatella vaccine, parvo/distemper vaccine (1-4 depending on age of dog), dewormer (2-4), monthly nexgard for flea and tick treatment.

Please fill out an application on our website www.goodlif3bullyrescue.org/adoption-application-1 or email goodlif3adoptions@gmail.com to find out more about this handsome short legged dude!

animal.description:
Lebron is living in a foster home. Submit an application from our website and then make an appointment to meet him.

Lebron is not eligible for foster and will be a straight adoption.

Age: ~8 months 
Weight: ~39lbs
Housebroken: Working on it! He needs to be on a strict schedule
Crate trained: 
Dog sociability: Friendly with dogs on walks
Cat sociability: Unknown
Kids: Friendly with kids, but can be mouthy/jumpy/humpy - so recommended for older kids only
Ideal home: An active home that can work on training as he is an energetic and adolescent pup!

If Lebron could spend 80% of his time outside - he would! This young guy loves to play with all the dogs and humans alike! He is a young dog - so lots of good energy and will need an adopter that can exhaust his exuberance in healthy ways. He thrives when given jobs to do such as enrichment toys. Roll some treats up in a paper towel roll, or sprinkle some snacks on the ground and let him "find it! Lebron would thrive with a dog pal either in his home or access to nearby friends/doggy daycare. When he gets overly amped up, or if he gets bored, his adolescent tendencies may appear. He also loves to chew and may need to be redirected to the right items to chomp on. This kid has been learning a lot in foster care and would love an adopter committed to working on his training.

animal.description:
Haiku is an 11-year-old lab mix who is looking for the perfect home to live out her glory days.  The thing she loves most is to spend time with her people. She would love to find someone who feels the same way about her! Wherever you are and whatever you are doing, she’d like to be close by laying in her dog bed. Haiku gets along with both dogs and cats. She is extremely mild mannered and barely makes a peep.  Haiku is potty trained and sleeps through the night.  She thrives with a consistent schedule.  Although she is older, Haiku is in great spirits and in generally good health.  Her main age related issue is arthritis in her spine and hips.  For this reason, she will need to remain on an aid, such as Rimadyl, for the remainder of her life.  Will you give this girl a chance to show you she’s worth it?

Note: Haiku is a bit on the skinny side currently, but continues to gain!  With her being older and having arthritis, gaining weight is something that takes time.  She has made great progress, but due to her age, we felt it was more important for her to find forever vs spending months gaining weight in her foster home.

Please visit halfwaythererescue@gmail.com for information on meeting and/or adopting Haiku!

Please contact Jo Ellen (hwbdogrescue@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Jinx is an adorable 3-month-old Chihuahua and blend who weighs approximately 3.6 pounds. Jinx initially is shy but once you offer him treats, he quickly displays his affectionate and playful nature.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more) - not just until his puppy cuteness wears off.
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization. Like most puppies, he may chew on anything within his reach to include but not limited to baseboards, shoes, socks, children's toys, electrical cords, plants, etc.
His adoption fee is $300. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccinations, Bravecto, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and adults dogs are tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
This puppy is in Tennessee. Adoption Donation $250 if picked up in TN, $300 plus transport fee for out of state adoptions.

Wonderful puppy Wren is a fun and active 5-month-old, Pit Bull Terrier / Australian Kelpie mix (best guess). She is 23 pounds and a fantastic canine companion. Wren is seeking an energetic family where she can go for walks, hikes, and lots of adventures. She is working on basic training in her foster home, and is treat motivated, so a continuation of this would be ideal. Wren is already crate and house trained, and is learning sit. She is a big fan of toys, and says any and all kinds will do. Wren has a stunning look that is quite unique, and we think she will be a gorgeous adult dog. She is good with other pets when given a slow and proper intro, so a playmate of her similar temperament and size would be okay for her new home. If you think you might be a perfect fit for Wren, apply to adopt today!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: http://aarf-tn.com/adopt/adoption-apps/

If you have questions that are not covered in the profile, visit the Pet Inquiry Form: http://aarf-tn.com/contact/pet-inquiry-form/.

THIS PET IS FOSTERED IN TENNESSEE! We do list and adopt our pets nationwide. Typical transport cost to the Northeast is $160. Due to interstate adoption regulations, we are not able to adopt to RI and MA state residents.

A.A.R.F. (All About Rescue and Fixin' Inc.) http://aarf-tn.com/ is a non-profit, 501(c)(3) no kill animal rescue organization located in the Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee. A.A.R.F. is comprised of unpaid volunteers and survives only on public donations. Thank you for thinking adoption first!

Prior to adoption, all canines and felines are spayed or neutered, have received their age appropriate vaccinations, have been de-wormed for common parasites, and have received treatment for prevention of fleas and ticks. All canines over the age of 6 months have been tested for heartworm. All canines are put on heartworm prevention as soon as possible - this means dogs as soon as they are tested negative. Puppies are put on prevention immediately. All felines, regardless of age, have been tested for Feline Leukemia/FIV. Each animal receives a health check by a licensed veterinarian prior to adoption. Anything else found will be treated by our organization prior to adoption.

animal.description:
Morty is a 14 week old lab mix. he's roughly 15-20 pounds at this time. he's come to us as a stray puppy, has had no formal training and lives in a shelter like environment so all his training would need to come from his new home. he has average energy for his age and size and plays well with all other dogs and humans and would probably do well with cats with proper introduction.

He is currently in Fort Worth, TX but can make the trek to Olympia, WA scheduled to arrive on Saturday Feb 6th with a pre-adoption which is the only way to secure that he will for sure go home with you! Pre-Adoption means getting your app in, approved and paying the adoption fee to secure the ride. His adoption fee is $450 which covers his neuter, vaccinations, HW testing, chipping, health certificate and transport fees. All our dogs come with a 30 day, money back, trial period to make sure they are the right fit in your environment. Tall Tails Rescue has a commitment to these dogs for their lifetime and we hope you do too! If you are interested in pre-adoption you can click the link here or copy/paste and fill out the app to get started: https://form.jotform.com/PNWdogs/ttrt-pnw-ap

animal.description:
Meet Otis. He came to us from a hoarding situation and has been slowly learning to trust people and enjoy affection. Otis likes to play with other pups but he tends to have a rough style of play (lots of chase) that is overwhelming for certain dogs. He is shy with new people but is highly food motivated and has a moderately active energy level. Otis needs a quiet home with dog experience and without young children that will be patient with him as he learns how to be a household companion! He is apx. 1.5 years old. 

Thank you for showing interest in our dogs, however due to the recent influx of applications and emails we ask that you avoid sending emails asking if: a listed dog is still available, if we received your application, or if we have additional photos (we always post whatever we have). Due to the current pandemic we have been receiving a huge influx of interest and emails and appreciate your help in lessening the workload for our volunteers. 

PLEASE NOTE: If you are interested in adopting a dog or puppy, please follow the steps below and submit an application. If you have questions you must reach out to us as we do not have the capacity to individually contact all applicants. You may call 559-393-1946 between 6PM and 9PM if you have additional questions AFTER SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION. During this time we are only accepting appointments at our Kingsburg facility, so please do not apply for a dog if you are not willing to drive to us.

Our dogs may be met by appointment locally in Kingsburg. Copy and paste the link below to submit a pre-screen application for the dog of interest, or find the link on our website www.pawsitiveconnections.org. Due to the overwhelming amount of interest our dogs have been receiving during this time, we unfortunately will not be able to reach out to all applicants who apply. If you do not receive correspondence from us, it is likely a reflection of the amount of applications we received. 

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScGSOxbGTIIintrGXUi8H-ddLv41aA0XUbELmNi0YhUIWQHRA/viewform

Adoption fee will include spay/neuter, microchip, rabies vaccine (dependent on age), bordatella vaccine, parvo/distemper vaccine (1-4 depending on age of dog), dewormer (2-4), monthly nexgard for flea and tick treatment.

animal.description:
Please contact Jo Ellen (hwbdogrescue@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Somer is a beautiful 5-year-old Great Dane. She is a sweet and quiet girl who would make a loyal companion.

Mystic has been diagnosed with heartworm infection. Dogs acquire heartworm infections when they are bitten by a mosquito that was infected with heartworm larvae.Dogs with heartworm infection live happy, high quality lives as long as they are given appropriate care. Heartworm infection is relatively common in the United States so we are in need of caring adopters like you that are willing to open their home to a dog with heartworm infection. We think that our heartworm dogs have just as much to offer their new adopters as any other dog and they deserve a chance at life. Adopters will receive all the necessary medications needed to complete the heartworm treatment protocol.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, 6-months of Coraxis, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and adults dogs are tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Gaia is a beautiful 3-year-old Great Dane. She is an active and playful dog and her ideal home would be able to provide her with appropriate daily exercise and training. Because of her size, she would not be suitable for a home with smaller dogs as they may find her rough play as overwhelming.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)

You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.

Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.

Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.

Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and adults dogs are tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

All people inquiring about pets listed as Courtesy Listings on the EAPL website and/or EAPL posting adoption boards should contact the current pet owner/rescue/shelter for answers to any questions and for final approval and placement. Please DO NOT CONTACT EAPL about courtesy listings. The pet owner/rescue/shelter and new owner shall make all arrangements on transferring the pet, information on history, vaccines, etc.

If you are interested in learning more about Willow, please call Annette at 713.416.9563 or email

jamm0808@gmail.com

with your contact information. There will be an adoption fee of $200 to be donated to EAPL.

Willow is a 4-year-old white shepherd mix that is about the cutest dog you have ever seen. Our family rescued her about 3 years ago and we live in Evergreen. She loves her humans and is very playful, energetic, and super smart, so she learns tricks very quickly. She also loves to snuggle and play with her toys (she is particularly fond of playing tuggie). Unfortunately, Willow does not get along with other dogs or cats in the home and needs to be an only dog. She is also an anxious dog, so she will need lots of love and patience. It breaks our heart to have to rehome Willow as she is a part of our family, and we want to ensure we find her a loving home where she can thrive. Willow is spayed and weighs about 45 pounds. Her shots are up to date. If you are interested in learning more about Willow, please call Annette at 713.416.9563 or email

jamm0808@gmail.com

with your contact information. There will be an adoption fee of $200 to be donated to EAPL.

animal.description:
COSTANZA - ID#A045411
Hi! My name is COSTANZA. I am a neutered male, black and brown Labrador Retriever and Rottweiler. The shelter staff think I am about 2 years old. I have been at the shelter since Jan 12, 2021.

I LOVE TO: go for walks and run around and play in the yard
I HAVE: a very active personality.
I GET ALONG WELL WITH: other dogs that match my energy level.
I WOULD RATHER NOT: be left alone for long periods of time
I NEED: a yard at home.
I AM: a friendly, sweet dog that would be great for a family with kids.

STARTING THE ADOPTION PROCESS:

Thank you for your interest in adopting an animal. To begin the process you will need to access & submit an adoption application. 

You can access our adoption application at either PetProjectFoundation.org or on the City of San Clemente’s website, under the Animal Services option.  
An adoption application can be submitted to the shelter, via Fax at (949) 366-4765, via email to Animalservices@scdpanimalshelter.org, or dropped off at the shelter in the drop box, located by our front door.  The San Clemente – Dana Point Animal Shelter is located at 221 Avenida Fabricante in San Clemente.

We look forward to receiving your application and will be in contact with you via email.

The shelter is currently closed to walk-in public, due to the COVID-19 virus. 

Staff are on site during our regular business hours (below), to address phone calls,  offer shelter services by appointment only, as well as handle any/all animal control concerns.

Our regular business hours are as follows:  
Monday – Closed
Tuesday – 10-4
Wednesday – 10-4
Thursday – 10-4
Friday – 10-4
Saturday – 10-4
Sunday – 12-3
 
In person services are by appointment only, due to the COVID-19 virus, please contact the shelter at (949) 492-1617, for more information.

animal.description:
Please contact Jo Ellen (hwbdogrescue@aol.com) for more information about this pet.Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Caramelo is a handsome 3-year-old Labrador Retriever blend who weighs approximately 33 pounds. Caramelo was found as a stray in a small town in Mexico where he faced a sad life of starvation and abuse. A Good Samaritan in that area stepped in to change his fate and contacted our rescue for assistance. Caramelo initially is shy but once your offer him treats, he quickly displays his affectionate and loyal nature.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for his entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)
You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.
His adoption fee is $175. This includes his neuter surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, Tri-Heart Plus chewable tablet, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.
Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.
Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.
Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.
** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and adults dogs are tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.
Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time from the Austin area.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

animal.description:
Name: Kimber
Age, Weight Gender: 11 months, 30-35 lbs, Female
Dog friendly/required?: Yes/YES!
Cat Friendly: Yes
Fenced yard required?: No
Housetrained: yes
Crate trained: Yes
Children: ok
Temperament: Med/low energy, Shy

Hi, my name is Kimber. I am 11 months old and 30-35 lbs (and growing!) but in such a short time I haven't been treated very nice by humans. I came from a home that liked to keep lots of doggies but not care for them. As a result I have been working on growing my hair, gaining some weight, and confidence back. I've been doing a good job of that with my foster the last month; went from 22 lbs to at least 30!!. I am a sweet pup and with a little time and patience will be ok.  My fur foster sibling Maddie, my gosh I like her she is really helping me. Because of that,  a home with a second dog IS A MUST for me.

I sleep in the crate ok. Last night I woke up in the middle of the night and then crept in foster mom's bed and cuddled up with her until the morning. I am a sweet baby! Oh and I am fine with cats!

animal.description:
COURTESY POST!  GABE IS NOT A SOHO DOG.  PLEASE CONTACT THE OWNER DIRECTLY AT Ladonna102460@gmail.com.	
	
Gabe is a happy, healthy, young Australian Shepherd/Husky mix who needs to find a new home.  His current owner must move and the new landlord does not allow dogs.  Gabe is not yet 2 years old, he weighs 60 pounds, and he is neutered and up to date on all of his vaccines.  He has a nice blue merle coat, partially blue eyes and a full tail!  Gabe is super smart and he knows a lot of obedience commands.  He is also housebroken, crate-trained, loves to ride in the car and he walks very nicely on leash.   
Gabe loves people and is comfortable with adults and children.  He is a medium Velcro, medium-to-high energy young guy who loves to play fetch, chase a ball around the pool, play with toys, go for walks, have his feet washed, you name it!  He just loves people and attention!  Gabe has had no exposure to other dogs other than a very small dog in the home, and he has not been introduced to cats.
The ideal home for Gabe is fun and active, shared with someone who has the time to spend with him and who is looking for a forever best friend.  A fenced yard is important and children over the age of 10 are welcome.  If Gabe sounds like YOUR new best friend, please contact his owner directly at Ladonna102460@gmail.com.  Gabe currently lives in Pilot Mountain, NC.

Meet Lucy! She came to Homeward Trails from Fayette County, WV where she was originally found as a stray. After not being reclaimed by her previous owners, she was lucky to go to a foster who took great care of her and helped learn more about her. 

She is a playful gal, a herding type who likes to run and chase other dogs and toys. She is best with another active and higher energy dog, and best in a home without cats or little animals. Isn't she adorable? Make an appointment to meet her this weekend! 

Adoption Coordinator: Adoption Center staff
Location: Adoption Center
The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee INCLUDES spay/neuter and microchip.

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please fill out our dog adoption questionnaire and e-mail it to adoptioncenter@homewardtrails.org 

PLEASE VISIT THIS WEBSITE TO FIND THE ADOPTION QUESTIONNAIRE:
http://www.homewardtrails.org/adopt-a-pet/adoption-forms/

Meet Deacon! He came to Homeward Trails from Fayette County, WV where he was originally found as a stray. He was wandering around a rural church community who began taking care of him and looking after him. He was sweet and gentle with the family in the community, and they generously offered to pay for his vaccines and neuter prior to coming to Homeward Trails.

Because of his past, Deacon is best in a home with a fenced yard and quieter area. He's not used to the hustle and bustle of city life, and will need some time to adjust to a home with more noise. He is happy and content to relax and stroll around the neighborhood or roam someones backyard.

He is a chill guy, happy to meet other dogs and very sweet with people. Make an appointment to come meet him! 

Adoption Coordinator: Adoption Center staff
Location: Adoption Center
The adoption fee for this dog is $475. This fee INCLUDES spay/neuter and microchip.

We are proud to partner with the following veterinarians who offer a free first exam for your animal, exclusively for HT adopters: Caring Hands Animal Hospital, Palisades Veterinary Clinic, Sunshine Animal Hospital and Clarendon Animal Care and all VCA Animal Hospitals.

Additionally, any VCA hospital will cover illnesses up to $250 at no cost to any Homeward Trails adopter.

We also provide free online workshop with a professional dog trainer at Fur-Get Me Not within the first 30 days of adopting - just for HT adopters in the Arlington/Alexandria/Falls Church/DC area. Start your new dog out on the right foot with this valuable, expert guidance FREE!

You can save animals like this one by becoming a foster! Fosters are like way stations between high kill shelters and forever homes. We need fosters so that we can save dogs before they are euthanized at the shelters. If you are interested in becoming a foster, please check out our information about fostering by visiting http://www.homewardtrails.org/foster-a-pet/dog-and-cat-foster-program

Frankie is a cuddly girl who is quickly overcoming her anxieties and growing into a happy dog. She is extremely food motivated and, because of that, easy to train; her behavior is already improving and she is learning new tricks with the help of tasty treats. She is house broken and on her way to being crate trained. Frankie wants to be a lap dog and is never far from a human to pet her and rub her ears. She is a playful girl and gaining confidence at the park and in the home. She loves to snooze on the couch and follow her human around. She is untested with cats but excellent with other dogs, men and kids. She will be an excellent pet.

Frankie will need a home with another confident dog.

Adoption Coordinator: Lauren T
Location: Foster

The adoption fee for this dog/puppy is $475. This fee includes spay/neuter and microchip.

Meet Todd and Diana! This sweet bonded pair comes to Homeward Trails from Fayette County, WV. Unfortunately, they were surrendered to the shelter (through no fault of their own!) after some hardships with their first family. Their story is sad, but they are clearly a fun and health duo, used to playtime and very sweet with new people. 

Todd is about 5 years old, 50 lbs and a neutered male, while Diana is 2 years old, 65 lbs and a spayed female. Check out this cute video of them as well. Their foster says they have settled in well, they love to play outside, go running, explore the backyard and snuggle up indoors. They seem sweet and resilient, with some minor signs of previous trauma, but very adaptable and happy dogs!

animal.description:
TILLY is affectionate, smart, playful and friendly.  She has good play skills and she's good with dogs and cats. She loves to be cuddled and petted and play. Tilly was born on one of the reservations we work with. Under her beautiful black coat is an even more beautiful tan undercoat :-) She's eager to learn, good candidate for agility.

Her adoption fee includes her spaying, vaccine series, rabies, deworming, microchip. She was born Sept 16, 2020.

** Do you live in our adopting area? ** Do you have another young playful friendly male dog of similar adult size? ** If yes to both questions, then please proceed with the application process below! :-)

We have specific adoption and Covid rules listed below.

Revised adoption policy
Due to Covid -19 pandemic and social distancing requirements, we've revised our adoption policy. 

First, please email (desertpawsnm@gmail.com) to inquire before you fill out the online application to see if the pet is still available. (Please do not call or text). We'll send you a link to the application.

We are unable to do multi-dog/cat meetgreets or adoption events at this time or bring multiple animals to your house to choose from, so please only inquire if you're serious about adopting this particular animal. If you're just shopping around with several shelters and rescues, please let us know this. 

If your application is approved (which "could" take up to one week) then we will contact you to set up a Zoom chat or ph call to answer questions/clarify anything and set up a day/time to bring the pet to you. 

Since we can't come into the home/yard due to Covid-19, we ask that you send us pics /video of your home/yard/living area/current pets. 

We will discuss with you about meeting your other pets. At the meeting/adoption at your house (outside) please wear a mask (as will we), keep to a properly distanced social distance and have hand sanitizer and your own leash.

We adopt locally to Central Abq, Santa Fe, Los Alamos and Rio Rancho. No out of area adoptions inquiries please. No young children for our adoptions please. Puppies MUST adopt to families that have another young friendly playful dog of similar breed size when grown. 

The animals are fostered and our foster families like to know their fosters are happy, healthy, and cared for during their lifetime. We appreciate staying in touch periodically (just a pic, holiday card, social media, pics/videos  etc will make our work worthwhile :-))

Our volunteers and adoption board are working diligently with an overload of inquiries since Covid to match families and forever pets. Our workload on the reservations has also increased. We're sorry, but if you email us with questions that are already answered here or fill out an application that does not fit the parameters of our procedures we will not be replying to you. Thank you for your understanding on this!

Thank you - we look forward to hearing from you and having another furbaby united with a furever family!

animal.description:
ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS
Fenced yard

My name is Hugo..I was found on the porch of a nice person that tried to find my family and had no luck so I am looking for a new one. Let me tell you a little about me...I am about 10 years old, I weigh appx 20lbs, I am good with kids and other dogs and I think cats too but I would have to ask my foster mom what she considers good. I am mostly housebroken but still learning. I hate being crated and I will definitely let you know that. I do much better with a baby gate in a room if you don't want to to roam the house at first. I have old man issues...I have arthritis and need pain meds when the weather is bad. It's actually best if I have them all the time for awhile. They aren't expensive and they make me feel so much better. I had a horrible ear infection but that is gone now. My foster mom says I am the cutest dog ever created, there's not an aggressive bone in my body, I am a very happy boy and I love to eat. I also love watching TV.. and snuggling on the couch, of course.

If you would like to meet Hugo send is an email to theloveofk9s@yahoo.com and we will get back with you as quick as we can. 

Adoption donation pays for all vetting...my neuter, a heart worm test, all vaccinations, deworming, flea prevention, a microchip and a wellness exam.

Scamper came into the shelter with his brother Scout. He is just under a year old, loves everyone he meets, and will be ready to leave after his neuter appt on 2/5. He is up to date on his vaccines and weighs approx 40#. 



FOR ADOPTERS: please contact Kelly, our Adoption Coordinator, with any questions at taylorcodogs@gmail.com or inquire directly via Petfinder. There is a link to our online ADOPTION APPLICATION on our Petfinder home page. You may also request an application via email. Paper copies are available at our shelter.
We always recommend a meet and greet with our dogs available for adoption. We are not able to assess dogs with cats since we are set up for dog intakes only. If you have cats, we advise a proper introduction while keeping the dog on leash in your home.
We are volunteer-based, so please be patient with our response time.

FOR RESCUES: Taylor County is rescue friendly! If you are a rescue, please contact our Rescue Coordinator, Diana, at deed1123@aol.com

DONATIONS: We are always in need of donations to help care for our dogs. We feed IAMS Adult Mini Chunks (green bag) and IAMS Smart Puppy. If you can assist financially, please mail a check payable to Taylor County Humane Society at PO Box 243, Grafton WV 26354 or visit our website to donate via PayPal. http://www.tchswv.com/donations/

animal.description: HOLY FLOOF! Dunkin has been a friend of Swamp's for awhile now and we are so excited to officially welcome him into the swampie family. Dunkin is a total charmer and ladies man (just ask the ladies at our vet who were fawning all over him), he loves other dogs, and doesn't mind cats that don't mind him! We have Dunkin on a strict diet and activity schedule as he weighs in at 95 lbs and needs to lose at least 20 of those. But we love a chonky boy and are thrilled to help get him back to his healthiest and most fit self! He needs a family that is as dedicated to keeping him active as they are giving him endless love. animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Please contact Jenny Cope (giveadogahome@live.com) for more information about this pet.

Be sure to read ALL information provided.

A PET IS FOR LIFE -
THINK ABOUT THE INVESTMENT!

KHUSHI was saved by a small rescue based in Kabul, Afghanistan. She had a severe case of pyometra (an infection of the womb) her womb was so swollen that it was starting to literally fall out of her. Emergency, life saving surgery was made and this lucky girl is alive due to the care and expertise of the rescue and veterinarians in Kabul.

Once recovered Khushi and her friend Noqrah were flown into the US where they waited in a boarding facility for transport up to Maine. They arrived at GaDaH on 25th January 2021.

Khushu is spayed, rabies, core vaccines, de-wormed, heartworm and tick disease tested negative, monthly preventatives and microchipped. At the time of her export/import examination she weighed she weighed around 43.00 pounds and has an estimated date of birth 15 March 2018.

We cannot say for sure what breed she is, so we expect families to do their own research on her look and size and decide what breed you think she is and if you have the lifestyle suitable for her needs.

For all that this sweet girl has been through, she is doing amazing, to think just over a week ago she was in Afghanistan, endured 48 hours traveling to US, then in a boarding facility for a few days and then driven for 1.5 days up to Maine and is a happy-go-lucky girl.

Khushi is a dog that you can not look at and not smile, she is so happy, she is so loving and affectionate, she has beautiful thick, soft fur and loves to cuddle and give kisses. Khushi lived with some female dogs whilst in Kabul and travelled to the rescue with Noqrah a young female dog and was great. At the rescue she was in the house and did seem to be a little protective of her area and would bark at the other dogs. This didn't seem to be an aggressive manner, but more of warning them to keep out of her space - which the dogs respected. After a couple of days I relocated her to the back sectioned off part of the kennel communal area, she has more space, a sofa, I put the TV on so she can used to that and she can interact with the other rescue dogs through the gate panel.

This girl is beyond a sweetheart, she would be happy to be the only dog, or with a bit of slow introductions share her new family and home with another dog, I think the rescue with so many dogs it is somewhat overwhelming for her, which again considering all she has been through is to be expected.

In Kabul, Khushi was around cats and she was great, however, we cannot say how she would be around livestock. She has a very sweet demeanor and deserves the best life has to offer.

We are looking for a family that go on hikes, walks, treks, adventures, to the beach, the lake, anywhere and everywhere that is fun and would give this beauty a wonderful fun filled life. She is going to need training, she is not fully house-trained, but does use pee-pads if they are put down - she just needs to learn to let her family know she needs to go outside. Khushi
is going to be a medium/large high energy dog and so she needs an active family who already have an adventurous and active lifestyle they can incorporate her into. She is a smart girl and so training and continued mental stimulation is also very important to make sure she gets the healthy, both physical and mental lifestyle that she needs and deserves.

More pictures and possible video's can be found on his page on the rescue website.

You MUST understand that dogs need time to decompress and adapt to their new environment and home. It is a HUGE transition they make from the kill shelter, being vetted, on transport for 3 days and arriving in Maine where the temperature and such is very different to what they have only known. In rescue there is what is known as the "3 Point Rule" Days 1-3 your dog is stressed, anxious, confused as to where they are now. Weeks 1-3 your dog is adjusting, settling in, learning things. At the 3 month point, your dog understands they are home, and have built up a trusting relationship where they feel loved and secure.

All dogs are fed Rachael Ray Nutrish PEAK Natural Dry Dog Food, Grain Free Western Grasslands Recipe with Bison. Rachael Ray Nutrish Peak Dog Food receives the Dog Food Advisor's second-highest tier rating of 4.5 stars.

Khushi is available for adoption for an adoption fee of $750, the higher adoption fee is to help cover the costs of her going through all the import/export certifications and the cost of her flight, boarding and transport to the rescue. This fee, obviously doesn't come close to covering these costs, but is a help.

This fee is not negotiable and is used to cover the rescue costs of pulling, vetting, health certificate, transport from Texas to Maine, monthly preventatives, supplements, food, general day to day cost of running a brick and mortar rescue and anything else that is needed. Canadian adopters need to know that customs charge 15% taxes when entering into Canada.

Due to borders being closed, it is up to families to call the US and Canadian borders to find the current details on border crossing. Animal Welfare is deemed essential in the US, but quarantine rules entering back into Canada must be followed.

If you feel that you have the heart and home to give this precious soul a wonderful life, please go to our website, under the ADOPTION INFO tab, complete, then submit the APPLICATION. Our process takes around 1-2 days, and ensuring your references are aware that we will be calling, could speed up the process. Once you have been approved, we discuss any questions in regards to the dog you are wanting to adopt, then you complete and submit the contract, make payment and then we can work out the pick up / transport arrangements.

Please do NOT submit an application if you are not looking to take home a new best friend within the next few weeks.

https://www.giveadogahome-sanantonio.org/forms/form?formid=5838

ALL Dogs are LOCATED AT THE RESCUE IN SEBEC, MAINE. We post in various states along the east coast and Canada where we have had lots of successful adoptions to enable more exposure for these beautiful saved souls. Families will need to be prepared to travel to the rescue to meet and take home their new best friend. Sebec is located just outside the towns of Dover-Foxcroft and Milo (approx 8 miles) and approx 45 miles from Bangor. There are also lots of hotels, motels, pet friendly accommodations and wonderful camp-sites for the more adventurous families and what a great way to get to know your new best friend.

Click here to watch a video of KHUSHI - Afghan pup.

animal.description:
8lb, 5 year old Grant is a fun loving, energetic, spicy little boy. With a short black and tan coat, ears with a mind of their own, and enough personality for 3 dogs, we guess he is a mix of chihuahua, miniature pinscher, dachshund, terrier, or something in between.

Grant is most often found bouncing around the house gathering up any toy in sight, or relentlessly asking the other dogs to play. He acts like a puppy and gets along with tolerant dogs that match his energy.

Originally a stray with an unknown past, he can be unsure of new people and will mouth or nip at hands and feet that move too quickly towards him, and although this behavior is mild at the moment, we strongly urge his new family to enroll in some positive reinforcement obedience and behavior training. We do not believe he will be a match for homes with children or cats at this time, but he has the potential to be a great family dog with the right guidance. Currently, he will bite out of fear when being picked up, but if someone sits on the ground he will often crawl into their lap and allow being picked up that way. He just needs time and consistency to overcome his fear.

Grant would make a great agility, flyball, or barn hunt dog - he definitely needs plenty of exercise and a job!

He is a healthy boy - up to date on vaccines, neutered, microchipped, and has had a recent dental with full bloodwork. All he needs now is a great adopter with the energy to match!

Please fill out an application and we will call you once approved to set up a meet and greet. If you have any questions, email director@canineestates.com or call 727-412-0558

animal.description:
Sidney is a cloud-white, sweet 10 year old, 16lb russell terrier mix lady. She was found as a stray in Lake County and has been blossoming nicely under our care. Sidney had some benign facial papilloma tumors which we had removed and although her fur is almost completely regrown, her pictures do not do her justice.

She is a little bit anxious when left alone, starting to show some signs of dementia, but friendly with all people and some mellow dogs; she would likely be fine with kids and cats as well. We would not place her with younger dogs as she has some balance issues and does not take kindly to rough housing. Sidney had to have an eye removed under our care, and has a cataract in her remaining eye that is beginning to interfere with her vision, but she gets around very well, and her nose works just fine(she is VERY food motivated)! She has a slight heart murmur that does not require medication yet (common with older dogs) and has had full bloodwork with a recent dental.

All she needs now is a comfortable bed and lots of love fur-ever. She is also available as a hospice foster, where you provide love and a home, and we will take care of her medical expenses for her remaining years.

Visits by appointment for approved applicants only, call 727-412-0558 or Email director@canineestates.com

animal.description:
Sora is looking for a forever home! He is about a year old and is a German Sheperd/Black Lab mix! 

 

Before considering adding Sora to your family, please note that KPAL Rescue has a mandatory adoption process in place which includes a background check and a home visit. More information on our adoption process can be found in our pinned post, please read that (and this adoption post) in their entirety - our process cannot be waived.

 

Sora is a sweet, young boy that would love to have a big yard to run around in. He would do best in a home that could give him structure; a schedule with daily physical and mental stimulation would help this boy thrive. Sora is leash-trained, potty-trained, and knows basic commands. When left unattended, Sora does best in a kennel as he has shown signs of being destructive when left home alone to free roam. He would need further training if his family would like him to free roam the house. Sora does well with most dogs, has never met cats, and has been great with children! 

 

Sora is being by fostered by Karen, we appreciate her so much! 

 

If youre interested in adopting Sora, our adoption process is outlined in our pinned post and on our website: www.kpalrescue.org/pet-adoption/. Our Adoption Application can also be found on that website.

 

KPAL Rescue dogs are fully vetted (vaccinated, microchipped, etc.) and spayed/neutered, there will be an adoption fee of $300 so that we can continue to help other animals in need. As always, donations are also very appreciated. Serious inquires only, please, and feel free to share.

animal.description:
Please note that due the volume of applications, we are unable to respond to all applicants and ONLY those being considered will be contacted. We thank you for your understanding. The adoption application link is posted below and the adoption process is outlined on the website.  Animatch asks that you read the Adoptee’s bio in its entirety before applying to ensure you meet the requirements for the dog.

Well, hello there, I’m Doe from Whapmagoostui and I rolled in with my two pups (Stag and Buck) who already have homes all lined up).  Guess what?  I’m ready for my next big adventure.  No need to worry about me coming out of my shell …. I’m turbo charged and ready for some action.  I’m an 80-lb dog who acts like a 10 lb pooch.  Because I am such an attention hog, I am always ready to launch myself at humans (in a friendly way, of course).   Animatch does not want to see anyone get bowled over or have their arm pulled out of its socket, so let’s sign me up for obedience training using positive reinforcement asap. Show me a tasty treat and you will soon have my full attention.  Having a safe enclosed yard where I can get rid of some of my energy before my walk would be ideal.  I just need to find a loving home with patient people who will have the time and compassion to help me be the best dog that I can be.  Since I’m not completely finished taking care of my pups, I have not been tested with other dogs.  But one thing I know for sure …. no cats or small critters allowed in my house!  Kids should be older because until I get some training under my fur; they will spend a lot of time being knocked on their butts.  I am not a dog for the inexperienced and if you know Shepherds that would be even better.  If you’re ready for a hilarious, fun-loving, huge bundle of joy then you’ve got to meet this girl!  Fill in the Adoption Form and ask for Doe.

animal.description:
ADOPTION REQUIREMENTS
Fenced yard
Can be an only dog in the right home

As you can see my name is Sergio. I was turned in to an animal control facility when my owner was no longer able to care for me. This is what my foster mom says about me.....

Sergio is a 5 year old Chihuahua/doxie mix. Sergio weighs about 11-12 pounds. He is a very unique reddish brown. He is very sweet and loving. He is house trained if he is taken out regularly. In yucky weather, he sometimes prefers to be leash walked. He is learning to not fear the leash. It takes him a little time to warm up to a person but once he does, he will be the most loving and loyal companion ever! He likes to play spend his days playing with his stuffed toys and cuddling. He likes other dogs just fine but can also be an only as long as his isn't home alone all day every day.


If you would like to meet Sergio, please send us an email to theloveofk9s@yahoo.com and we will get back to you as soon as possible.

 His adoption donation pays for all vetting... neuter, microchip, all vaccinations, a heart worm test, deworming, flea prevention and a wellness exam

animal.description:
I want to be your new BUDDY! Like the elf, I have traveled a long way (from Texas) to find my new family here in beautiful, colorful Colorado! 

I love to go for walks and jogs, to play with other dogs, and play fetch with my humans. I love to chew on ice cubes and to snuggle with my foster furparents! I sleep through the night, peacefully in my crate without making a peep. I have a funny personality and am full of love, all I want to do is give you all the kisses. I have learned Sit, am pretty well potty trained, and can definitely learn lots more since I am very motivated by treats! 

I hope I find my furever family soon! Will it be with you?

animal.description:
Handsome Mr. Debo finds himself in-search of a new forever family of his own. Debo is 3 years old, and is THEE happiest and cuddliest pittie boy around! He loves his people (and loves to just be around them) so much that he smiles every time they come home for the day. He could spend hours on end just lounging on the couch, cuddling and napping (on the lap of his person, of course!) the day away. Debo also love, love, LOVES his toys! Although, it has been determined that he can typically only have hard/durable toys and chew toys...as he will destroy any other kinds of toys and attempt to eat them before his humans can get them away from him. One of Debos favorite pastimes is playing fetch, and he would love to have a fenced-in backyard where he could run freely and play fetch with his human to his hearts content! Because Debo can get pretty possessive over his balls/bones, and because he doesnt fancy sharing his toys (with other dogs and/or human strangers), we are recommending that he be the only dog in the home. He is currently in a home with other dogs, and has been in several scuffles over his unwillingness to share. We truly believe that he would thrive going to a home where he could be his humans one and only...to soak up all of the attention and live his best life. He also needs to go to a home either without children, or with children who are old enough to understand not to attempt to randomly take his toys away from him. Once he trusts people, he will drop and leave his toys/ball for his human friends when he is asked. Debo is completely potty-trained and crate-trained, knows his basic commands, and loves to just be in the presence of his humans. He typically does ok encountering other dogs (out on walks, etc.), but does need to be introduced to them slowly and in a controlled environment. He will also need to go to a cat-free home. Debo is such a special boy who deserves everything good that this world has to offerand we would love to find him a forever where he can be the apple of his persons eye. In return, he promises endless love and cuddles. Just ask for Debo! 
 
If you are interested in adopting Debo, please submit a general application at https://newleashdogrescue.com/.
 
**Debos $200 adoption fee includes his neuter, vaccinations, heartworm test, and microchip.

animal.description:
Howdy has lived his whole life on and off a chain without shelter until our partners in Louisiana stepped in.  His previous owner kicked him in the jaw and left it to get infected.  His jaw may have been broken at one time and he's currently getting a work up so that he has a great future. Despite his abuse Howdy is a really happy and very sweet young 12 month old boy.  He is a little unsure of new things at first but he is not fearful. He is a super playful and happy boy who loves to explore the toy box and pick out a favorite or two. He is a quick learner and willing to please.  He is good with dogs and cats.  He likes to have his ears rubbed and to sit by your side.  He is just a handsome little fellow and will make a gentle human a wonderful companion! He is full grown at 28 lbs.
Reviewing applications now. Apply at http://www.saveadog.org/applytoadopt.asp

animal.description: Meet Kit! Kit is a 1.5 year old male, weighing around 45lbs with similarities to an Staffordshire Terrier mix! Sweet Kit was found as a stray on the streets of TN and a volunteer was trying to feed him to get him into rescue. He has a scar on his head that looks to be from a chemical burn or some kind of abuse he endured on the streets, yet he remains trusting of people and very loving. He was super friendly and was happy to go with the rescuer to get care. He has been loving life in foster care, getting regular meals, and getting love. Kit's foster mom says, "Kit is a sweet ball of energy, he loves cuddling and will sit and lay down for treats. He likes to be outside but needs practice walking on a leash. He LOVES to play and run. His true personality comes out when he feels safe." His perfect fit would be a family he can adventure with! He temp tested well with other dogs, but is currently in a foster home by himself. He is house trained and crate trained. Kit is fully vetted and neutered and ready to go on his next adventure! Kids ages 8+ recommended so he doesn't knock anyone over. He would love an active family or a fenced in yard. To apply to adopt Kit, please go to www.charliescrusaders.org

0520063

I am very active, so I need lots of physical and mental stimulation. I am suitable for single family homes with yards.


Meet Kaleb he is around 18 months old. A neutered Aussie/ mix. He is a fun-loving boy and a total sweetheart. Kaleb spent 4 weeks training full-time with the CCI prison training program and has lots of tricks to show you! They taught him how to walk on a leash, basic tricks like sit-stay-down, cool tricks like five bucks (one paw), ten bucks (two paws), roll over, (Hes still working on that one.) . Kaleb is crate trained and house trained. He will make an amazing addition to a loving family. Kaleb loves to play but can settle down and just hang out too. Slow introductions to new humans and other dogs are recommended. But once he knows you he loves any attention. He loves to have his belly and ears rubbed. Kaleb is super smart and is continuing to learn new things every day. He is working on going potty in one specific area in the yard. Sometimes he forgets but it wont take him long to remember. Kaleb would thrive in a home with older children (older than 10 years old) who can work with him on his training and love and play with him. As foster parents we love Kaleb. But feel he needs a bigger more active family to meet his needs. 

He's athletic, so he needs at least a 6 ft fence--anything smaller, and he'll jump it.
